"use strict";(self.webpackChunkducnguyen_96=self.webpackChunkducnguyen_96||[]).push([[1477],{10:function(n){n.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"what-is-rabbitmq","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/what-is-rabbitmq","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-10-07-rabbitmq-overview/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-10-07-rabbitmq-overview/index.md","title":"RabbitMQ overview","description":"Ngu\u1ed3n//www.youtube.com/watch?v=GN0xHSk2P8Q","date":"2021-10-07T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 7, 2021","tags":[{"label":"rabbitmq","permalink":"/blog/tags/rabbitmq"},{"label":"backend","permalink":"/blog/tags/backend"}],"readingTime":2.875,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"nextItem":{"title":"M\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 thu\u1eadt ng\u1eef ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn m\xe0 m\xecnh g\u0103p xuy\xean su\u1ed1t qu\xe1 tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c","permalink":"/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec"}},"content":"Ngu\u1ed3n: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GN0xHSk2P8Q\\n\\n## Message Broker - Message Queue\\n\\nTr\u1edf l\u1ea1i v\u1edbi ki\u1ebfn tr\xfac Monolithic, c\xe1c components c\u1ee7a app b\xf3 bu\u1ed9c ch\u1eb7t ch\u1ebd v\u1edbi nhau. V\xed d\u1ee5 v\u1edbi m\u1ed9t \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng b\xe1n l\u1ebb, ta c\xf3 m\u1ed9t checkout service c\u1ea7n k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi inventory service th\xec th\u01b0\u1eddng s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft b\u1eb1ng TCP connection, ngay khi checkout g\u1eedi message \u0111\u1ebfn inventory th\xec n\xf3 c\u1ea7n ngay reply tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi \u0111\u1ebfn v\u1edbi t\xe1c v\u1ee5 ti\u1ebfp theo, ho\u1eb7c t\u1ec7 h\u01a1n n\u1ebfu inventory crash th\xec n\xf3 s\u1ebd c\u1ed1 g\u1eafng g\u1eedi request cho t\u1edbi khi thi\u1ebft l\u1eadp connection, ho\u1eb7c n\u1ebfu c\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u checkouts x\u1ea3y ra c\xf9ng l\xfac th\xec inventory service kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 theo k\u1ecbp.\\n\\n- Decouple\\n\\nV\xe0 \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 l\xfac message queue \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o ra, n\xf3 s\u1ebd \u0111\u1ee9ng gi\u1eefa 2 service c\u1ea7n giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau (ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n checkout service v\xe0 inventory service). L\xfac n\xe0y checkout message s\u1ebd g\u1eedi 1 message \u0111\u1ebfn broker v\xe0 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n t\xe1c v\u1ee5 kh\xe1c ngay. Inventory sau khi \u0111\xe3 s\u1eb5n s\xe0ng th\xec c\xf3 th\u1ec3 consume message \u0111\xf3, process theo message v\xe0 ngay l\u1eadp t\u1ee9c consume message ti\u1ebfp theo. MQ gi\xfap t\xe1ch bi\u1ec7t 2 service ra.\\n\\n- Scalable\\n\\n\u0110\u1ed3ng th\u1eddi n\xf3 c\u0169ng gi\xfap scale app c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n, v\xed d\u1ee5 n\u1ebfu s\u1ed1 checkout t\u0103ng l\xean qu\xe1 nhi\u1ec1u th\xec b\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 t\u0103ng s\u1ed1 instances c\u1ee7a inventory l\xean v\xe0 s\u1ed1 l\u01b0\u1ee3ng message cho m\u1ed7i instance s\u1ebd gi\u1ea3m xu\u1ed1ng.\\n\\n- Performant\\n\\nMQ c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1eb7t \u1edf 1 m\xe1y ri\xeang, n\xf3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 gi\u1ea3m t\u1ea3i cho c\xe1c t\xe1c v\u1ee5 m\xe0 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh b\u1edfi web app gi\xfap app \u0111\u1ea1t performence t\u1ed1t h\u01a1n.\\n\\n## RabbitMQ\\n\\n![rabbitmq](/img/blogs/rabbitmq.png)\\n\\nL\xe0 m\u1ed9t tri\u1ec3n khai c\u1ee7a AMQP(Advanced Message Queueing Protocol) message model - 091.\\n\\nThay v\xec g\u1eedi message tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp \u0111\u1ebfn message queue, n\xf3 s\u1ebd g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn m\u1ed9t exchange. M\u1ed9t exchange c\xf3 th\u1ec3 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ebfn nhi\u1ec1u queue v\xe0 m\u1ed7i queue c\xf3 th\u1ec3 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ebfn c\xe1c services kh\xe1c nhau.\\n\\nService g\u1eedi message \u0111\u1ebfn exchange --\x3e exchange \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi c\xe1c queues qua c\xe1c connections \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 bindings \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ref b\u1edfi binding key. C\xe1c consumer s\u1ebd subsribe \u0111\u1ebfn c\xe1c queues \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1eafng nghe message. RabbitMQ l\xe0 h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng bao g\u1ed3m exchange v\xe0 c\xe1c queue, RabbitMQ r\u1ea5t linh ho\u1ea1t nh\u1edd c\xe1c lo\u1ea1i exchanges kh\xe1c nhau m\xe0 n\xf3 h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3.\\n\\n- Fanout exchange: Message \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1eeb service s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c duplicate v\xe0 g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c queues.\\n- Direct exchange: Message \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1eeb service ch\u1ee9a routing key, n\xf3 s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c map v\u1edbi binding key \u0111\u1ec3 chuy\u1ec3n t\u1edbi queue.\\n- Topic exchange: Gi\u1ed1ng v\u1edbi direct exchange nh\u01b0ng n\xf3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 match t\u1eebng ph\u1ea7n (partial match) ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n \\"ship.shoes\\" v\xe0 \\"ship.any\\"\\n- Header exchange: Routing key s\u1ebd b\u1ecb b\u1ecf qua v\xe0 message \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c route theo header.\\n- Default exchange: Routing key match v\u1edbi t\xean c\u1ee7a queue.\\n\\nC\xe1ch g\u1eedi v\xe0 nh\u1eadn message trong RabbitMQ \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c defined b\u1eb1ng metadata l\xe0 c\xe1c key v\xe0 lo\u1ea1i exchange n\xean app v\xe0 developer c\xf3 th\u1ec3 control nhi\u1ec1u h\u01a1n.\\n\\n- Cloudy friendly: C\xf3 th\u1ec3 deploy b\u1eb1ng container, deploy nh\u01b0 1 cluster.\\n- Cross-language: V\xed d\u1ee5 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 produce b\u1eb1ng Go v\xe0 consume b\u1eb1ng JS, Python,...\\n- Security: Support FASL, LDAP, TLS\\n- Acks: Comsumer ack message gi\xfap broker bi\u1ebft r\u1eb1ng consumer \u0111\xe3 nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c message, v\xe0 lo\u1ea1i b\u1ecf n\xf3 ra kh\u1ecfi queue. \u0110i\u1ec1u n\xe0y tr\xe1nh t\xecnh tr\u1ea1ng miss message ho\u1eb7c loss message v\xec n\u1ebfu consumer kh\xf4ng ack th\xec message v\u1eabn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c gi\u1eef trong queue.\\n- Greate management: C\xf3 management UI, CLI.\\n- Plug-in: C\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u plug-ins \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ph\xe1t tri\u1ec3n b\u1edfi c\u1ed9ng \u0111\u1ed3ng opensource."},{"id":"mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-09-07-common-terminologies/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-09-07-common-terminologies/index.md","title":"M\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 thu\u1eadt ng\u1eef ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn m\xe0 m\xecnh g\u0103p xuy\xean su\u1ed1t qu\xe1 tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c","description":"1. Website Defacement l\xe0 g\xec ?","date":"2021-09-07T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 7, 2021","tags":[{"label":"terminology","permalink":"/blog/tags/terminology"}],"readingTime":3.425,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"RabbitMQ overview","permalink":"/blog/what-is-rabbitmq"},"nextItem":{"title":"Javascript in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/javascript-in-a-nutshell"}},"content":"## 1. Website Defacement l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\n**Website Defacement** l\xe0 m\u1ed9t lo\u1ea1i t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng website m\xe0 n\xf3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n thay \u0111\u1ed5i giao di\u1ec7n c\u1ee7a to\xe0n b\u1ed9 site ho\u1eb7c ch\u1ec9 1 page. C\xe1ch th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n l\xe0 ch\xfang s\u1ebd x\xe2m nh\u1eadp v\xe0o web server(b\u1eb1ng c\xe1ch ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 web shell) v\xe0 thay th\u1ebf site \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c host b\u1eb1ng site c\u1ee7a ch\xfang.\\n\\nM\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch: Ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn nh\u1ea5t l\xe0 truy\u1ec1n b\xe1 th\xf4ng tin nh\u1eb1m k\xedch \u0111\u1ed9ng bi\u1ec3u t\xecnh ch\xednh tr\u1ecb hay t\xf4n gi\xe1o.\\n\\n## 2. Backward compatibility l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\n**Backward compatibility** l\xe0 kh\u1ea3 n\u0103ng t\u01b0\u01a1ng th\xedch ng\u01b0\u1ee3c - m\u1ed9t thu\u1ed9c t\xednh c\u1ee7a h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng, s\u1ea3n ph\u1ea9m hay c\xf4ng ngh\u1ec7 m\xe0 cho ph\xe9p t\u01b0\u01a1ng th\xedch v\u1edbi m\u1ed9t h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng c\u0169 h\u01a1n.\\n\\nM\u1ed9t kh\xe1i ni\u1ec7m \u0111\u1ed1i ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\xe0 **forward compatibility**. L\xe0 m\u1ed9t thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf m\xe0 h\u01b0\u1edbng t\u1edbi t\u01b0\u01a1ng th\xedch v\u1edbi c\xe1c ti\xeau chu\u1ea9n hay s\u1ea3n ph\u1ea9m m\u1edbi trong t\u01b0\u01a1ng lai.\\n\\n## Same-origin policy l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\n**Same-origin policy** l\xe0 m\u1ed9t c\u01a1 ch\u1ebf b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt quan tr\u1ecdng \u0111\u1ec3 h\u1ea1n ch\u1ebf vi\u1ec7c 1 document hay 1 script \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c load m\u1edfi 1 origin c\xf3 th\u1ec3 t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\xe1c v\u1edbi resource c\u1ee7a 1 origin kh\xe1c. Hi\u1ec3u \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n h\u01a1n n\u1ebfu `https://abc.xyz ` mu\u1ed1n load \u1ea3nh t\u1eeb `https://cde.xyz` th\xec ph\u1ea3i th\xeam cde.xyz l\xe0 1 origin tr\xean header c\u1ee7a site.\\n\\nN\xf3 gi\xfap c\xf4 l\u1eadp nh\u1eefng documents kh\u1ea3 nghi, gi\u1ea3m b\u1edbt nguy c\u01a1 b\u1ecb t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng.\\n\\n## 3. Man in the middle attack l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\nTrong ng\xe0nh m\xe3 h\xf3a v\xe0 b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt m\xe1y t\xednh, **man-in-the-middle**, **monster-in-the-middle**, **machine-in-the-middle**, **person-in-the-middle** l\xe0 m\u1ed9t lo\u1ea1i t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng m\xe0 k\u1ebb t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng nghe l\xe9n ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 thay \u0111\u1ed5i giao ti\u1ebfp gi\u1eefa 2 b\xean m\xe0 h\u1ecd tin r\u1eb1ng m\xecnh \u0111ang n\xf3i giao ti\u1ebfp tr\u1ef1c ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau c\xf2n tr\xean th\u1ef1c t\u1ebf th\xec \u0111ang b\u1ecb \u0111i\u1ec1u khi\u1ec3n b\u1edfi k\u1ebb t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng.\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5: Alice mu\u1ed1n giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi Bob. Mallory mu\u1ed1n ng\u0103n ch\u1eb7n cu\u1ed9c h\u1ed9i tho\u1ea1i \u0111\u1ec3 nghe tr\u1ed9m v\xe0 c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0a cho Bob nh\u1eefng tin nh\u1eafn sai l\u1ec7ch.\\n\\n\u0110\u1ea7u ti\xean Alice s\u1ebd h\u1ecfi public key c\u1ee7a Bob. N\u1ebfu Bob g\u1eedi public key \u0111\u1ebfn Alice v\xe0 Mallory ng\u0103n ch\u1eb7n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\xec 1 cu\u1ed9c t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u. Mallory s\u1ebd g\u1eedi cho Alice 1 tin nh\u1eafn gi\u1ea3 m\u1ea1o l\xe0 t\u1eeb Bob nh\u01b0ng thay v\xec public key c\u1ee7a Bob th\xec Mallory g\u1eedi public key c\u1ee7a Mallory.\\n\\nAlice tin \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 key c\u1ee7a Bob n\xean \u0111\xe3 m\xe3 h\xf3a tin nh\u1eafn c\u1ee7a Alice theo key kia v\xe0 g\u1eedi l\u1ea1i cho Bob. 1 l\u1ea7n n\u1eefa th\xec Mallory l\u1ea1i ch\u1eb7n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tin nh\u1eafn n\xe0y v\xe0 gi\u1ea3i m\xe3 tin nh\u1eafn \u0111\xf3, sau \u0111\xf3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 thay \u0111\u1ed5i hay kh\xf4ng th\xec t\xf9y v\xe0 l\u1ea1i 1 l\u1ea7n n\u1eefa m\xe3 h\xf3a tin nh\u1eafn \u0111\xf3 b\u1eb1ng key m\xe0 Bob c\u1ed1 g\u1eedi cho Alice. Khi Bob nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tin nh\u1eafn m\u1edbi th\xec Bob tin r\u1eb1ng tin nh\u1eafn \u0111\xf3 \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1eeb Alice.\\n\\n## 4. MIME types l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\nL\xe0 m\u1ed9t ti\xeau chu\u1ea9n \u0111\u1ec3 ch\u1ec9 ra \u0111\u1ecbnh d\u1ea1ng c\u1ee7a t\xe0i li\u1ec7u, file hay l\xe0 1 ph\xe2n lo\u1ea1i c\xe1c bytes. Browsers s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng MIME type \u0111\u1ec3 quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh c\xe1ch x\u1eed l\xfd 1 URL v\u1eady n\xean vi\u1ec7c servers g\u1eedi \u0111\xfang MIME type trong Content-Type header r\u1ea5t l\xe0 quan tr\u1ecdng. N\u1ebfu n\xf3 kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5u h\xecnh \u0111\xfang th\xec browser c\xf3 th\u1ec3 hi\u1ec3u sai n\u1ed9i dung files v\xe0 sites s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\xednh x\xe1c, c\xe1c file \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea3i v\u1ec1 s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed l\xfd sai.\\n\\nMIME type \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n nh\u1ea5t ch\u1ee9a 1 `type` v\xe0 1 `subtype` \u0111\u1ec1u l\xe0 string v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi nhau b\u1eb1ng `/`: `type/subtype`\\n\\n**type** th\xec \u0111\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho ph\xe2n lo\u1ea1i chung c\u1ee7a data ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 `video` ho\u1eb7c `text`. **subtype** th\xec ch\u1ec9 r\xf5 ch\xednh x\xe1c lo\u1ea1i c\u1ee7a data, ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ed1i v\u1edbi `text` th\xec subtype l\xe0 `plain` (plain text) ho\u1eb7c `html` ho\u1eb7c `calendar`.\\n\\n**parameter** l\xe0 1 thu\u1ed9c t\xednh kh\xf4ng b\u1eaft bu\u1ed9c c\xf3 th\u1ec3 th\xeam v\xe0o \u0111\u1ec3 cung c\u1ea5p th\xeam chi ti\u1ebft:\\n\\n```html\\ntext/plain;charset=UTF-8\\n```\\n\\n## 5. Click-jacking attack l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\nClick-jacking l\xe0 m\u1ed9t th\u1ee7 \u0111o\u1ea1n \u0111\xe1nh l\u1eeba user click v\xe0o 1 \u0111\u01b0\u1eddng link hay 1 button,... kh\xe1c v\u1edbi c\xe1i m\xe0 user ngh\u0129. \u0110i\u1ec1u n\xe0y c\xf3 th\u1ec3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\xe1nh c\u1eafp x\xe1c minh \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp ho\u1eb7c \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea5y quy\u1ec1n c\u1ee7a user \u0111\u1ec3 c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t malware."},{"id":"javascript-in-a-nutshell","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/javascript-in-a-nutshell","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-30-javascript-in-a-nutshell/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-30-javascript-in-a-nutshell/index.md","title":"Javascript in a nutshell","description":"Do b\xe0i vi\u1ebft c\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u m\u1ee5c v\xe0 d\xe0i n\xean b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ecdc nh\xecn v\xe0o Table Of Content (TOC) \u1edf side-bar b\xean ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ecdc m\u1ee5c m\xecnh quan t\xe2m nh\xe9.","date":"2021-08-30T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 30, 2021","tags":[{"label":"javascript","permalink":"/blog/tags/javascript"}],"readingTime":15.795,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"M\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 thu\u1eadt ng\u1eef ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn m\xe0 m\xecnh g\u0103p xuy\xean su\u1ed1t qu\xe1 tr\xecnh h\u1ecdc t\u1eadp v\xe0 l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c","permalink":"/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec"},"nextItem":{"title":"Authentication in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/authentication-in-a-nutshell"}},"content":"Do b\xe0i vi\u1ebft c\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u m\u1ee5c v\xe0 d\xe0i n\xean b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ecdc nh\xecn v\xe0o Table Of Content (TOC) \u1edf side-bar b\xean ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ecdc m\u1ee5c m\xecnh quan t\xe2m nh\xe9.\\n\\nTham kh\u1ea3o: [javascript.info](https://javascript.info)\\n\\n## Variables\\n\\n### var\\n\\n**\\"var\\" kh\xf4ng c\xf3 block scope**\\n\\n```javascript\\nif (true) {\\n  var test = true; // d\xf9ng \\"var\\" thay \\"let\\"\\n}\\n\\nalert(test); // true, var kh\xf4ng c\xf3 block scope n\xean n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c k\xe9o ra kh\u1ecfi block scope.\\n```\\n\\nN\u1ebfu m\u1ed9t block n\u1eb1m trong 1 function th\xec `var` s\u1ebd tr\u1edf th\xe0nh bi\u1ebfn `function-level`\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sayHi() {\\n  if (true) {\\n    var phrase = \\"Hello\\";\\n  }\\n\\n  alert(phrase); // works\\n}\\n\\nsayHi();\\nalert(phrase); // ReferenceError: phrase is not defined\\n```\\n\\n**\\"var\\" ch\u1ea5p nh\u1eadn khai b\xe1o l\u1ea1i**\\nN\u1ebfu ch\xfang ta khai b\xe1o 1 bi\u1ebfn v\u1edbi `let` 2 l\u1ea7n trong c\xf9ng 1 scope th\xec s\u1ebd l\u1ed7i\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user;\\nlet user; // SyntaxError: \'user\' has already been declared\\n```\\n\\nV\u1edbi var, ch\xfang ta c\xf3 th\u1ec3 khai b\xe1o l\u1ea1i bao nhi\xeau l\u1ea7n t\xf9y \xfd.\\n\\n```javascript\\nvar user = \\"Pete\\";\\n\\nvar user = \\"John\\"; // this \\"var\\" does nothing (already declared)\\n// ...it doesn\'t trigger an error\\n\\nalert(user); // John\\n```\\n\\n**\\"var\\" c\xf3 th\u1ec3 khai b\xe1o sau khi s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng**\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sayHi() {\\n  phrase = \\"Hello\\";\\n\\n  alert(phrase);\\n\\n  var phrase;\\n}\\nsayHi();\\n```\\n\\n\u0110o\u1ea1n code tr\xean t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u01b0\u01a1ng v\u1edbi\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sayHi() {\\n  var phrase;\\n\\n  phrase = \\"Hello\\";\\n\\n  alert(phrase);\\n}\\nsayHi();\\n```\\n\\n\u0110\xe2y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 `hoisting` (k\xe9o l\xean), v\xec t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 `var` \u0111\u1ec1u \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c k\xe9o l\xean \u0111\u1ea7u c\u1ee7a 1 h\xe0m.\\n**Khai b\xe1o th\xec \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c k\xe9o l\xean c\xf2n g\xe1n gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb th\xec kh\xf4ng**\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sayHi() {\\n  alert(phrase);\\n\\n  var phrase = \\"Hello\\";\\n}\\n\\nsayHi();\\n```\\n\\n\u0110o\u1ea1n code tr\xean t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u01b0\u01a1ng v\u1edbi\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sayHi() {\\n  var phrase; // declaration works at the start...\\n\\n  alert(phrase); // undefined\\n\\n  phrase = \\"Hello\\"; // ...assignment - when the execution reaches it.\\n}\\n\\nsayHi();\\n```\\n\\n### let\\n\\n**\\"let\\" c\xf3 block scoped ch\u1ee9 kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i global scope hay local scope**\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet greeting = \\"say Hi\\";\\nlet times = 4;\\nif (times > 3) {\\n  let hello = \\"say Hello instead\\";\\n  console.log(hello); // \\"say Hello instead\\"\\n}\\nconsole.log(hello); // hello is not defined\\n```\\n\\n**\\"let\\" cho ph\xe9p g\xe1n l\u1ea1i gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb, kh\xf4ng cho ph\xe9p khai b\xe1o l\u1ea1i**\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet greeting = \\"say Hi\\";\\nconsole.log(greeting); //\\"say Hi\\"\\n\\ngreeting = \\"say Hello instead\\";\\nconsole.log(greeting); //\\"say Hello instead\\"\\n-----------------------------------------------------\\nlet greeting = \\"say Hi\\";\\nlet greeting = \\"say Hello instead\\"; // error: Identifier \'greeting\' has been declared\\n```\\n\\n**\\"let\\" c\xf3 hoisted kh\xf4ng ?**\\nTham kh\u1ea3o \u1edf [\u0111\xe2y](/blog/javascript-in-a-nutshell/#hoisted)\\n\\n### const\\n\\n`const` th\xec gi\u1ed1ng v\u1edbi `let` \u1edf ch\u1ed7 n\xf3 c\u0169ng c\xf3 block scope v\xe0 hoisting, tuy nhi\xean n\xf3 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 g\xe1n l\u1ea1i gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb c\u1ee7a bi\u1ebfn. Tuy nhi\xean \u0111\u1ed1i v\u1edbi bi\u1ebfn d\u1ea1ng reference (object, array, function) th\xec ta v\u1eabn c\xf3 th\u1ec3 c\u1eadp nh\u1eadt \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb thu\u1ed9c t\xednh c\u1ee7a bi\u1ebfn \u0111\xf3.\\n\\n```javascript\\nconst greeting = {\\n  message: \\"Hello\\",\\n  number: \\"five\\",\\n};\\ngreeting.message = \\"say Hello instead\\";\\nconsole.log(greeting); // {message:\\"say Hello instead\\",number:\\"five\\"}\\n```\\n\\n## Hoisted\\n\\nT\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c khai b\xe1o trong javascript (var, let, const, function, function\\\\*, class) \u0111\u1ec1u \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c `hoisted`. C\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 n\u1ebfu m\u1ed9t bi\u1ebfn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c khai b\xe1o trong 1 scope, th\xec trong scope \u0111\xf3, \u0111\u1ecbnh danh c\u1ee7a n\xf3 s\u1ebd lu\xf4n tr\u1ecf \u0111\u1ebfn bi\u1ebfn \u0111\xf3. Xem v\xed d\u1ee5 d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y:\\n\\n```javascript\\nx = \\"global\\";\\n// function scope:\\n(function() {\\n    x; // not \\"global\\"\\n\\n    var/let/\u2026 x;\\n}());\\n// block scope (not for `var`s):\\n{\\n    x; // not \\"global\\"\\n\\n    let/const/\u2026 x;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n\u1ede tr\xean ta c\xf3 x \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c khai b\xe1o \u1edf global scope, tuy nhi\xean \u1edf trong function v\xe0 block kia \u0111\u1ec1u khai b\xe1o l\u1ea1i bi\u1ebfn \u0111\xf3 \u1edf d\u01b0\u1edbi c\xf9ng c\u1ee7a block v\xe0 n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c neo l\xean \u0111\u1ea7u, ch\xednh v\xec th\u1ebf m\xe0 x kh\xf4ng c\xf3 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb l\xe0 \\"global\\".\\n\\n## Loops\\n\\n### Labels for break/continue\\n\\n\u0110\xf4i khi ta mu\u1ed1n break kh\u1ec9 nhi\u1ec1u v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p l\u1ed3ng nhau c\xf9ng l\xfac.\\n\\n```javascript\\nfor (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\\n  for (let j = 0; j < 3; j++) {\\n    let input = prompt(`Value at coords (${i},${j})`, \\"\\");\\n\\n    // what if we want to exit from here to Done (below)?\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nalert(\\"Done!\\");\\n```\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5 ch\xfang ta c\u1ea7n 1 c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ec3 d\u1eebng x\u1eed l\xfd khi ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng cancel input. Break th\xf4ng th\u01b0\u1eddng s\u1ebd ch\u1ec9 d\u1eebng 1 v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p. Khi \u0111\xf3 ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd c\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ebfn label.\\n\\n```\\nouter: for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\\n\\n  for (let j = 0; j < 3; j++) {\\n\\n    let input = prompt(`Value at coords (${i},${j})`, \'\');\\n\\n    // if an empty string or canceled, then break out of both loops\\n    if (!input) break outer; // (*)\\n\\n    // do something with the value...\\n  }\\n}\\nalert(\'Done!\');\\n```\\n\\n\u1ede \u0111o\u1ea1n code tr\xean, `break outer` \u0111\xe3 t\xecm l\xean v\xe0 th\u1ea5y 1 label v\u1edbi t\xean `outer` v\xe0 break v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p \u0111\xf3.\\n\\nCh\xfang ta c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng label cho c\u1ea3 `continue`, l\xfac \u0111\xf3 th\xec code s\u1ebd th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n nh\u1ea3y \u0111\u1ebfn v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p ti\u1ebfp theo c\u1ee7a loop \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\xe1nh nh\xe3n.\\n\\n## Functions\\n\\n### A Function Declaration can be called earlier than it is defined.\\n\\n```javascript\\nsayHi(\\"John\\"); // Hello, John\\n\\nfunction sayHi(name) {\\n  alert(`Hello, ${name}`);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n```javascript\\nsayHi(\\"John\\"); // error!\\n\\nlet sayHi = function (name) {\\n  // (*) no magic any more\\n  alert(`Hello, ${name}`);\\n};\\n```\\n\\n### Khi n\xe0o s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Function Declaration vs Function Expression.\\n\\nNh\u01b0 m\u1ed9t quy lu\u1eadt, khi khai b\xe1o 1 function th\xec \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean ta c\xe2n nh\u1eafc s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Function Declaration. N\xf3 gi\xfap ch\xfang ta s\u1eafp x\u1ebfp code d\u1ec5 d\xe0ng h\u01a1n v\xec ch\xfang ta c\xf3 th\u1ec3 g\u1ecdi n\xf3 tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c khai b\xe1o.\\n\\nNh\u01b0ng n\u1ebfu Function Declaration kh\xf4ng ph\xf9 h\u1ee3p v\xec 1 s\u1ed1 l\xfd do ho\u1eb7c ch\xfang ta c\u1ea7n 1 khai b\xe1o c\xf3 \u0111i\u1ec1u ki\u1ec7n th\xec khi \u0111\xf3 n\xean s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Function Expression.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet age = prompt(\\"What is your age?\\", 18);\\n\\nlet welcome =\\n  age < 18\\n    ? function () {\\n        alert(\\"Hello!\\");\\n      }\\n    : function () {\\n        alert(\\"Greetings!\\");\\n      };\\n\\nwelcome(); // ok now\\n```\\n\\n## The JavaScript \\"this\\" keyword\\n\\n- In a method, this refers to the owner object.\\n- Alone, this refers to the global object.\\n- In a function, this refers to the global object.\\n- In a function, in strict mode, this is undefined.\\n- In an event, this refers to the element that received the event.\\n- Methods like call(), and apply() can refer this to any object.\\n\\n## Object references and copying\\n\\n### Khi m\u1ed9t bi\u1ebfn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\xe1n v\xe0o 1 object th\xec n\xf3 kh\xf4ng l\u01b0u tr\u1eef object \u0111\xf3 m\xe0 l\xe0 \\"\u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 b\u1ed9 nh\u1edb\\" - n\xf3i c\xe1ch kh\xe1c l\xe0 \\"1 reference\\" t\u1edbi object.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = {\\n  name: \\"John\\",\\n};\\n```\\n\\nObject \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u \u1edf \u0111\xe2u \u0111\u1ea5y trong b\u1ed9 nh\u1edb v\xe0 bi\u1ebfn user c\xf3 1 reference t\u1edbi n\xf3.\\n\\nCh\xfang ta c\xf3 th\u1ec3 xem user nh\u01b0 1 t\u1edd gi\u1ea5y c\xf3 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 c\xf3 object tr\xean \u0111\xf3. Khi ch\xfang ta th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n action l\xean object ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 `user.name` th\xec JavaScript engine s\u1ebd nh\xecn l\xean \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 \u0111\xf3 v\xe0 t\xecm \u0111\u1ebfn object th\u1ef1c s\u1ef1 trong b\u1ed9 nh\u1edb v\xe0 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n h\xe0nh \u0111\u1ed9ng l\xean \u0111\xf3.\\n\\n### Khi m\u1ed9t bi\u1ebfn object \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c cope th\xec \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c copy ch\u1ee9 kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i c\xe1i object m\xe0 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 tr\u1ecf \u0111\u1ebfn, v\xec v\u1eady object s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c nh\xe2n b\u1ea3n l\xean.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = { name: \\"John\\" };\\n\\nlet admin = user;\\n\\nadmin.name = \\"Pete\\"; // changed by the \\"admin\\" reference\\n\\nalert(user.name); // \'Pete\', changes are seen from the \\"user\\" reference\\n```\\n\\n### Cloning and merging, Object.assign\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = { name: \\"John\\" };\\n\\nlet permissions1 = { canView: true };\\nlet permissions2 = { canEdit: true };\\n\\n// copies all properties from permissions1 and permissions2 into user\\nObject.assign(user, permissions1, permissions2);\\n\\n// now user = { name: \\"John\\", canView: true, canEdit: true }\\n```\\n\\n## Rest parameters and spread syntax\\n\\n### Rest parameters ...\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sum(a, b) {\\n  return a + b;\\n}\\n\\nalert(sum(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)); // 3\\n```\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction sumAll(...args) {\\n  // args is the name for the array\\n  let sum = 0;\\n\\n  for (let arg of args) sum += arg;\\n\\n  return sum;\\n}\\n\\nalert(sumAll(1)); // 1\\nalert(sumAll(1, 2)); // 3\\nalert(sumAll(1, 2, 3)); // 6\\n```\\n\\n### The \u201carguments\u201d variable\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction showName() {\\n  alert(arguments.length);\\n  alert(arguments[0]);\\n  alert(arguments[1]);\\n\\n  // it\'s iterable\\n  // for(let arg of arguments) alert(arg);\\n}\\n\\n// shows: 2, Julius, Caesar\\nshowName(\\"Julius\\", \\"Caesar\\");\\n\\n// shows: 1, Ilya, undefined (no second argument)\\nshowName(\\"Ilya\\");\\n```\\n\\n### Spread syntax\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet arr = [3, 5, 1];\\n\\nalert(Math.max(...arr)); // 5 (spread turns array into a list of arguments)\\n```\\n\\n## Lexical Environment\\n\\nTrong JavaScript, t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c function, code block {...}, v\xe0 c\u1ea3 file script \u0111\u1ec1u c\xf3 1 internal object li\xean k\u1ebft v\u1edbi ch\xfang \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u1ea9n \u0111i l\xe0 _Lexial Environment_\\n\\nObject Lexical Environment th\xec ch\u1ee9a 2 ph\u1ea7n:\\n\\n- Environment Record - l\xe0 m\u1ed9t object l\u01b0u tr\u1eef t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c bi\u1ebfn local v\xe0 c\xe1c thu\u1ed9c t\xednh c\u1ee7a n\xf3.\\n- M\u1ed9t reference \u0111\u1ebfn outer lexical environment \u0111\u1ec3 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi c\xe1c code b\xean ngo\xe0i block ho\u1eb7c function.\\n\\n\x3c!-- ![search-lexical-environment](/img/blogs/search-lexical-environment.png) --\x3e\\n\\nKhi m\u1ed9t \u0111o\u1ea1n code mu\u1ed1n truy c\u1eadp v\xe0o bi\u1ebfn th\xec inner Lexical Environment s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\xecm ki\u1ebfm \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean -> outer -> outer .... -> global one.\\n\\n## Closure\\n\\n![closure](/img/blogs/closure.png)\\nClosure l\xe0 m\u1ed9t function m\xe0 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 nh\u1edb c\xe1c bi\u1ebfn b\xean ngo\xe0i c\u1ee7a n\xf3 v\xe0 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 truy c\u1eadp ch\xfang. \u1ede m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 ng\xf4n ng\u1eef th\xec \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y l\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 function \u0111\xf3 ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c vi\u1ebft m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch \u0111\u1eb7c bi\u1ec7t. Nh\u01b0ng v\u1edbi JavaScript th\xec m\u1ecdi functions \u0111\u1ec1u l\xe0 closures.\\n\\nH\u1ea7u h\u1ebft th\xec m\u1ed9t Lexical Environment s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c lo\u1ea1i kh\u1ecfi b\u1ed9 nh\u1edb c\xf9ng v\u1edbi t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c bi\u1ebfn sau khi function \u0111\xe3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n xong v\xec kh\xf4ng c\xf3 references n\xe0o t\u1edbi n\xf3 n\u1eefa.\\n\\nTuy nhi\xean, n\u1ebfu c\xf3 m\u1ed9t function l\u1ed3ng nhau v\xe0 n\xf3 v\u1eabn reachable th\xec sau khi function k\u1ebft th\xfac, th\xec n\xf3 v\u1eabn c\xf3 c\xe1c property m\xe0 tr\u1ecf \u0111\u1ebfn lexical environment.\\n\\nNh\u01b0 v\xed d\u1ee5 \u1edf tr\xean, counter() sau khi \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\u1ea7n 1 n\xf3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n makeCounter() v\xe0 tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1 0, tuy nhi\xean th\xec counter v\u1eabn reachable v\xe0 do \u0111\xf3 c\xe1c bi\u1ebfn trong makeCounter v\u1eabn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c d\u1eef l\u1ea1i, v\xec th\u1ebf n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n g\u1ecdi counter() 1 l\u1ea7n n\u1eefa th\xec n\xf3 s\u1ebd tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1 1, ti\u1ebfp theo l\xe0 2, 3, ...\\n\\n## The \\"new Function\\" syntax\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction getFunc() {\\n  let value = \\"test\\";\\n\\n  let func = new Function(\\"alert(value)\\");\\n\\n  return func;\\n}\\n\\ngetFunc()(); // error: value is not defined\\n```\\n\\nT\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 function \u0111\u1ec1u nh\u1edb n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o ra \u1edf \u0111\xe2u nh\u1edd v\xe0o 1 thu\u1ed9c t\xednh \u0111\u1eb7c bi\u1ec7t l\xe0 `[[Environment]]`. N\xf3 tr\u1ecf \u0111\u1ebfn Lexical Environment n\u01a1i n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o ra.\\n\\nNh\u01b0ng n\u1ebfu function \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng synxtax `new Function` th\xec `[[Environment]]` c\u1ee7a n\xf3 s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c set \u0111\u1ec3 tr\u1ecf \u0111\u1ebfn glocal Lexical Environment ch\u1ee9 kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i Lexical Environment. So v\u1edbi h\xe0m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o 1 c\xe1ch th\xf4ng th\u01b0\u1eddng:\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction getFunc() {\\n  let value = \\"test\\";\\n\\n  let func = function () {\\n    alert(value);\\n  };\\n\\n  return func;\\n}\\n\\ngetFunc()(); // \\"test\\", from the Lexical Environment of getFunc\\n```\\n\\n## Property flags and descriptors\\n\\nNh\u01b0 ta \u0111\xe3 bi\u1ebft th\xec objects c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\u01b0u tr\u1eef thu\u1ed9c t\xednh, thu\u1ed9c t\xednh kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 1 c\u1eb7p `key-value` m\xe0 n\xf3 linh ho\u1ea1t h\u01a1n v\u1eady.\\n\\n### Property flags\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = {\\n  name: \\"John\\",\\n};\\n\\nlet descriptor = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(user, \\"name\\");\\n\\nalert(JSON.stringify(descriptor, null, 2));\\n/* property descriptor:\\n{\\n  \\"value\\": \\"John\\",\\n  \\"writable\\": true,\\n  \\"enumerable\\": true,\\n  \\"configurable\\": true\\n}\\n*/\\n```\\n\\nC\xe1c thu\u1ed9c t\xednh c\u1ee7a objects ngo\xe0i **value** th\xec c\xf2n c\xf3 3 attributes sau:\\n\\n- **writeable**: if `true` th\xec **value** c\xf3 th\u1ec3 thay \u0111\u1ed5i, c\xf2n kh\xf4ng th\xec ch\u1ec9 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 `read`\\n- **enumerable**: if `true` th\xec \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c list ra trong v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p v\xe0 ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i\\n- **configurable**: if `true` th\xec thu\u1ed9c t\xednh n\xe0y c\xf3 th\u1ec3 b\u1ecb deleted nh\u1eefng attributes c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1ec9nh s\u1eeda v\xe0 ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = {};\\n\\nObject.defineProperty(user, \\"name\\", {\\n  value: \\"John\\",\\n  // for new properties we need to explicitly list what\'s true\\n  enumerable: true,\\n  configurable: true,\\n});\\n\\nalert(user.name); // John\\nuser.name = \\"Pete\\"; // Error\\n```\\n\\nV\u1edbi defineProperty n\u1ebfu 1 attribute kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u1ecbnh th\xec n\xf3 s\u1ebd m\u1eb7c \u0111\u1ecbnh c\xf3 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb l\xe0 `false`.\\n\\n## Property getters and setters\\n\\nObject c\xf3 2 lo\u1ea1i thu\u1ed9c t\xednh l\xe0 `data properties` v\xe0 `accessor properties`\\n\\n### Getters and Setters\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = {\\n  name: \\"John\\",\\n  surname: \\"Smith\\",\\n\\n  get fullName() {\\n    return `${this.name} ${this.surname}`;\\n  },\\n\\n  set fullName(value) {\\n    [this.name, this.surname] = value.split(\\" \\");\\n  },\\n};\\n\\n// set fullName is executed with the given value.\\nuser.fullName = \\"Alice Cooper\\";\\n\\nalert(user.name); // Alice\\nalert(user.surname); // Cooper\\n```\\n\\n### Smarter getters/setters\\n\\nGetters/setters c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng nh\u01b0 `wrapper` cho 1 thu\u1ed9c t\xednh \u0111\u1ec3 t\u0103ng th\xeam quy\u1ec1n \u0111i\u1ec1u khi\u1ec3n.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet user = {\\n  get name() {\\n    return this._name;\\n  },\\n\\n  set name(value) {\\n    if (value.length < 4) {\\n      alert(\\"Name is too short, need at least 4 characters\\");\\n      return;\\n    }\\n    this._name = value;\\n  },\\n};\\n\\nuser.name = \\"Pete\\";\\nalert(user.name); // Pete\\n\\nuser.name = \\"\\"; // Name is too short...\\n```\\n\\n### Using for compatibility\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5 ta implement 1 object user nh\u01b0 sau:\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction User(name, age) {\\n  this.name = name;\\n  this.age = age;\\n}\\n\\nlet john = new User(\\"John\\", 25);\\n\\nalert(john.age); // 25\\n```\\n\\nNh\u01b0ng sau \u0111\xf3 ch\xfang ta quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh l\xe0 l\u01b0u `birthday` thay v\xec `age`, v\xec n\xf3 ch\xednh x\xe1c h\u01a1n v\xe0 ti\u1ec7n h\u01a1n. Nh\u01b0ng ta v\u1eabn mu\u1ed1n gi\u1eef l\u1ea1i thu\u1ed9c t\xednh age v\xec age c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u1edf nhi\u1ec1u n\u01a1i b\u1edfi nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi.\\n\\nTa s\u1ebd th\xeam `age` nh\u01b0 sau:\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction User(name, birthday) {\\n  this.name = name;\\n  this.birthday = birthday;\\n\\n  // age is calculated from the current date and birthday\\n  Object.defineProperty(this, \\"age\\", {\\n    get() {\\n      let todayYear = new Date().getFullYear();\\n      return todayYear - this.birthday.getFullYear();\\n    },\\n  });\\n}\\n\\nlet john = new User(\\"John\\", new Date(1992, 6, 1));\\n\\nalert(john.birthday); // birthday is available\\nalert(john.age); // ...as well as the age\\n```\\n\\n## Callbacks\\n\\nR\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u h\xe0m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5p b\u1edfi m\xf4i tr\u01b0\u1eddng ch\u1ea1y JS cho ph\xe9p b\u1ea1n schedule nh\u1eefng h\xe0nh \u0111\u1ed9ng b\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ed3ng b\u1ed9. N\xf3i c\xe1ch kh\xe1c l\xe0 nh\u1eefng h\xe0nh \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\xfang ta kh\u1edfi t\u1ea1o b\xe2y gi\u1edd, nh\u01b0ng sau n\xe0y m\u1edbi ho\xe0n th\xe0nh. V\xed d\u1ee5 1 trong nh\u1eefng function \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 `setTimeout`.\\n\\nXem v\xed d\u1ee5 d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y:\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction loadScript(src) {\\n  // creates a <script> tag and append it to the page\\n  // this causes the script with given src to start loading and run when complete\\n  let script = document.createElement(\\"script\\");\\n  script.src = src;\\n  document.head.append(script);\\n}\\nloadScript(\\"/my/script.js\\"); // the script has \\"function newFunction() {\u2026}\\"\\n\\nnewFunction(); // no such function!\\n```\\n\\n`script.js` ch\u1ee9a h\xe0m `newFunction()` v\xe0 ta c\u1ea7n ch\u1ea1y h\xe0m n\xe0y ngay sau khi `loadScript` th\xe0nh c\xf4ng. Hi\u1ec7n t\u1ea1i th\xec `loadScript` ch\u01b0a cung c\u1ea5p 1 c\xe1ch n\xe0o \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 theo d\xf5i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c vi\u1ec7c load script th\xe0nh c\xf4ng hay ch\u01b0a, loadScript ch\u1ea1y v\xe0 n\xf3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n ngay h\xe0m ti\u1ebfp theo d\xf9 script ch\u01b0a \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c load hay ch\u01b0a. Nh\u01b0ng ch\xfang ta c\u1ea7n bi\u1ebft khi n\xe0o load xong \u0111\u1ec3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng `newFunction()`. V\xe0 `callback` l\xe0 gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p l\xfac n\xe0y.\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction loadScript(src, callback) {\\n  let script = document.createElement(\'script\');\\n  script.src = src;\\n\\n  script.onload = () => callback(script);\\n\\n  document.head.append(script);\\n}\\n\\nloadScript(\'/my/script.js\', function() {\\n  // the callback runs after the script is loaded\\n  newFunction(); // so now it works\\n  ...\\n});\\n```\\n\\n## Promise\\n\\n1. \\"producing code\\" l\xe0 \u0111o\u1ea1n code m\xe0 c\u1ea7n th\u1eddi gian \u0111\u1ec3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh, ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 load data t\u1eeb network.\\n2. \\"consuming code\\" l\xe0 \u0111o\u1ea1n code m\xe0 mu\u1ed1n result sau khi producing code ho\xe0n th\xe0nh. Nhi\u1ec1u h\xe0m c\xf3 th\u1ec3 c\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ebfn result.\\n3. promise l\xe0 m\u1ed9t JS object m\xe0 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i \\"producing code\\" v\xe0 \\"consuming code\\".\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet promise = new Promise(function (resolve, reject) {\\n  // executor (the producing code, \\"singer\\")\\n});\\n```\\n\\nH\xe0m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c truy\u1ec1n v\xe0o Promise \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 `executor`. Khi m\u1ed9t Promise \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o ra th\xec executor ch\u1ea1y ngay. resolver v\xe0 reject l\xe0 2 callbacks m\xe0 JS t\u1ea1o ra, code c\u1ee7a ch\xfang ta ch\u1ec9 n\u1eb1m trong executor.\\n\\n![promise-1](/img/blogs/promise-1.png)\\n\\nKhi executor c\xf3 result th\xec n\xf3 s\u1ebd g\u1ecdi 1 trong 2 callbacks:\\n\\n- resolve(value) - n\u1ebfu job ho\xe0n th\xe0nh c\xf9ng v\u1edbi `value`.\\n- reject(error) - n\u1ebfu c\xf3 l\u1ed7i x\u1ea3y ra, error l\xe0 error object.\\n\\nT\xf3m l\u1ea1i: Executor s\u1ebd t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\u1ea1y ngay khi Promise \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o v\xe0 n\xf3 s\u1ebd c\u1ed1 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh c\xf4ng vi\u1ec7c. Khi n\xf3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh th\xec s\u1ebd g\u1ecdi `resolve` v\xe0 g\u1ecdi `reject` n\u1ebfu c\xf3 l\u1ed7i x\u1ea3y ra.\\n\\nPromise object ch\u1ee9a nh\u1eefng thu\u1ed9c t\xednh sau:\\n\\n- state - kh\u1edfi t\u1ea1o v\u1edbi `pending` sau \u0111\xf3 thay \u0111\u1ed5i th\xe0nh `fullfilled` ho\u1eb7c `rejected`\\n- result - kh\u1edfi t\u1ea1o v\u1edbi `undefined` sau \u0111\xf3 thay \u0111\u1ed5i th\xe0nh `value` ho\u1eb7c `error`\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5:\\n\\n```javascript\\nfunction loadScript(src) {\\n  return new Promise(function (resolve, reject) {\\n    let script = document.createElement(\\"script\\");\\n    script.src = src;\\n\\n    script.onload = () => resolve(script);\\n    script.onerror = () => reject(new Error(`Script load error for ${src}`));\\n\\n    document.head.append(script);\\n  });\\n}\\n\\nlet promise = loadScript(\\n  \\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/lodash.js/4.17.11/lodash.js\\"\\n);\\n\\npromise.then(\\n  (script) => alert(`${script.src} is loaded!`),\\n  (error) => alert(`Error: ${error.message}`)\\n);\\n\\npromise.then((script) => alert(\\"Another handler...\\"));\\n```\\n\\nCh\xfang ta c\xf3 th\u1ec3 th\u1ea5y ngay 1 v\xe0i l\u1ee3i \xedch c\u1ee7a promise so v\u1edbi callbacks:\\n\\n- Promises cho ph\xe9p ch\xfang ta l\xe0m theo th\u1ee9 t\u1ef1 t\u1ef1 nhi\xean h\u01a1n, v\xed d\u1ee5 loadScript(script) sau \u0111\xf3 th\xec `.then` \u0111\u1ec3 vi\u1ebft nh\u1eefng th\u1ee9 mu\u1ed1n l\xe0m v\u1edbi result.\\n\\n- \u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi callback th\xec ch\xfang ta ph\u1ea3i bi\u1ebft l\xe0m g\xec ti\u1ebfp theo v\u1edbi result ngay tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi loadScript \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi.\\n\\n## Promise API\\n\\n### Promise.all\\n\\nExecute nhi\u1ec1u promises \u0111\u1ed3ng th\u1eddi v\xe0 ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 \u0111\u1ec1u ho\xe0n th\xe0nh.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet promise = Promise.all([...promises...]);\\n```\\n\\n- N\u1ebfu c\xf3 b\u1ea5t c\u1ee9 promise n\xe0o trong array promises kia b\u1ecb rejected th\xec Promise.all s\u1ebd b\u1ecb reject c\xf9ng v\u1edbi l\u1ed7i, c\xe1c promise kh\xf4ng b\u1ecb l\u1ed7i s\u1ebd b\u1ecb ignore ch\u1ee9 k b\u1ecb cancel.\\n- Promise.all cho ph\xe9p c\xe1c gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i promise trong iterable.\\n\\n### Promise.allSettled\\n\\nExecute nhi\u1ec1u promises \u0111\u1ed3ng th\u1eddi v\xe0 ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 \u0111\u1ec1u ho\xe0n th\xe0nh, n\u1ebfu c\xf3 promise n\xe0o b\u1ecb l\u1ed7i th\xec v\u1eabn s\u1ebd ti\u1ebfp t\u1ee5c th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n v\xe0 theo d\xf5i nh\u1eefng promise c\xf2n l\u1ea1i.\\n\\n### Polyfill\\n\\nN\u1ebfu browser kh\xf4ng h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 Promise.allSetted th\xec ch\xfang ta c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m nh\u01b0 sau:\\n\\n```javascript\\nif (!Promise.allSettled) {\\n  const rejectHandler = (reason) => ({ status: \\"rejected\\", reason });\\n\\n  const resolveHandler = (value) => ({ status: \\"fulfilled\\", value });\\n\\n  Promise.allSettled = function (promises) {\\n    const convertedPromises = promises.map((p) =>\\n      Promise.resolve(p).then(resolveHandler, rejectHandler)\\n    );\\n    return Promise.all(convertedPromises);\\n  };\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Promise.race\\n\\nT\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 Promise.all nh\u01b0ng n\xf3 ch\u1ec9 ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi 1 promise ho\xe0n th\xe0nh ho\u1eb7c g\u1eb7p l\u1ed7i.\\n\\n### Promise.any\\n\\nT\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 Promise.race nh\u01b0ng ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi 1 promise \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c fulfilled.\\n\\n## Async/await\\n\\n`async` tr\u01b0\u1edbc 1 function c\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 function \u0111\xf3 s\u1ebd lu\xf4n tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1 1 promise. T\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb kh\xe1c \u0111\u1ec1u \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c wrapped trong 1 resolved promise.\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5, function d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y s\u1ebd tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1 1 resolved promise v\u1edbi gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb l\xe0 1\\n\\n```javascript\\nasync function f() {\\n  return 1;\\n}\\n\\nf().then(alert); // 1\\n```\\n\\n`await` s\u1ebd l\xe0m JS ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi 1 promise ho\xe0n th\xe0nh ho\u1eb7c g\u1eb7p l\u1ed7i.\\n\\n```javascript\\nasync function f() {\\n  let promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\\n    setTimeout(() => resolve(\\"done!\\"), 1000);\\n  });\\n\\n  let result = await promise; // wait until the promise resolves (*)\\n\\n  alert(result); // \\"done!\\"\\n}\\n\\nf();\\n```"},{"id":"authentication-in-a-nutshell","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/authentication-in-a-nutshell","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-29-authentication-in-a-nutshell/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-29-authentication-in-a-nutshell/index.md","title":"Authentication in a nutshell","description":"Nh\u01b0 \u0111\xe3 n\xf3i trong b\xe0i n\xe0y, http kh\xf4ng gi\u1eef tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i gi\u1eefa 2 l\u1ea7n request v\xec v\u1eady v\xed d\u1ee5 sau khi \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp sau, user \u0111\u1ebfn m\u1ed9t page n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 c\u1ea7n x\xe1c minh ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 setting th\xec user l\u1ea1i b\u1ecb y\xeau c\u1ea7u \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp l\u1ea7n n\u1eefa. Nh\u01b0ng v\u1edbi session ho\u1eb7c token authentication th\xec server c\xf3 th\u1ec3 nh\u1eadn bi\u1ebft l\xe0 user \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp v\xe0 n\xean \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5p quy\u1ec1n truy c\u1eadp.","date":"2021-08-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 29, 2021","tags":[{"label":"authentication","permalink":"/blog/tags/authentication"}],"readingTime":2.375,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Javascript in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/javascript-in-a-nutshell"},"nextItem":{"title":"Http in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/http-in-a-nutshell"}},"content":"Nh\u01b0 \u0111\xe3 n\xf3i trong b\xe0i [n\xe0y](/blog/http-in-a-nutshell/), http kh\xf4ng gi\u1eef tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i gi\u1eefa 2 l\u1ea7n request v\xec v\u1eady v\xed d\u1ee5 sau khi \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp sau, user \u0111\u1ebfn m\u1ed9t page n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 c\u1ea7n x\xe1c minh ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 setting th\xec user l\u1ea1i b\u1ecb y\xeau c\u1ea7u \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp l\u1ea7n n\u1eefa. Nh\u01b0ng v\u1edbi session ho\u1eb7c token authentication th\xec server c\xf3 th\u1ec3 nh\u1eadn bi\u1ebft l\xe0 user \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp v\xe0 n\xean \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5p quy\u1ec1n truy c\u1eadp.\\n\\n## Session based authentication\\n\\nSever t\u1ea1o v\xe0 l\u01b0u l\u1ea1i d\u1eef li\u1ec7u session \u1edf server v\xe0 l\u01b0u tr\u1eef session id tr\xean tr\xecnh duy\u1ec7t c\u1ee7a user.\\n\\n![sesssion-based-authentication](/img/blogs/session-based-authentication.png)\\n\\n- user \u0111\u1ebfn trang \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp v\xe0o g\u1eedi th\xf4ng tin \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp \u0111\u1ebfn server.\\n- server s\u1ebd t\u1ea1o 1 session v\xe0 l\u01b0u tr\u1eef l\u1ea1i, sau \u0111\xf3 g\u1eedi session id v\u1eeba t\u1ea1o cho user.\\n- user g\u1eedi request l\u1ea5y profile c\u1ee7a user (k\xe8m session id).\\n- server so s\xe1nh session id v\u1edbi session data \u0111\xe3 l\u01b0u \u0111\u1ec3 nh\u1eadn bi\u1ebft user v\xe0 g\u1eedi l\u1ea1i \u0111\xfang profile c\u1ee7a user n\xe0y.\\n\\nV\u1eady c\xf3 th\u1ec3 n\xf3i tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i c\u1ee7a user \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u \u1edf server.\\n\\n## Token based authentication\\n\\n\u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi token based authentication th\xec tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i c\u1ee7a user \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u \u1edf client v\xe0 ph\u01b0\u01a1ng ph\xe1p n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c khuy\xean d\xf9ng h\u01a1n so v\u1edbi ph\u01b0\u01a1ng ph\xe1p session based.\\n![token-based-authentication](/img/blogs/token-based-authentication.png)\\n\\n- user \u0111\u1ebfn trang \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp v\xe0o g\u1eedi th\xf4ng tin \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp \u0111\u1ebfn server.\\n- D\u1eef li\u1ec7u c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c m\xe3 h\xf3a d\u01b0\u1edbi d\u1ea1ng JWT (Json Web Token) b\u1eb1ng 1 \u0111o\u1ea1n m\xe3 v\xe0 g\u1eedi v\u1ec1 client.\\n- JWT \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u \u1edf client (h\u1ea7u h\u1ebft l\xe0 \u1edf localStorage).\\n- user g\u1eedi request l\u1ea5y profile c\u1ee7a user (k\xe8m jwt).\\n- Server nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c JWT, s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111o\u1ea1n m\xe3 \u0111\xe3 d\xf9ng \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ea1o ra JWT \u0111\u1ec3 gi\u1ea3i m\xe3 v\xe0 c\xf3 th\xf4ng tin ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng.\\n- Server g\u1eedi l\u1ea1i \u0111\xfang profile c\u1ee7a user.\\n\\n## OAuth\\n\\n_V\u1ec1 c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n th\xec oauth l\xe0 m\u1ed9t ph\u01b0\u01a1ng th\u1ee9c ch\u1ee9ng th\u1ef1c, m\xe0 nh\u1edd \u0111\xf3 m\u1ed9t web service hay m\u1ed9t application b\xean th\u1ee9 3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng \u0111\u1ec3 truy c\u1eadp v\xe0o t\xe0i nguy\xean ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng n\u1eb1m tr\xean m\u1ed9t d\u1ecbch v\u1ee5 n\xe0o \u0111\xf3._\\n\\n![oauth-flow](/img/blogs/blog-open1.webp)\\n\\n\u1ede \u0111\xe2y user ch\xednh l\xe0 ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng app c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n, consumer l\xe0 app c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n - Yelp v\xe0 service provider c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0 google, facebook,...\\n\\nKhi ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng click v\xe0o \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp v\u1edbi google th\xec app c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd direct b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ebfn google, n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n ch\u01b0a \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp google th\xec s\u1ebd ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp, sau \u0111\xf3 google s\u1ebd h\u1ecfi b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ed3ng \xfd trao quy\u1ec1n truy c\u1eadp cho Yelp. Sau khi b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ed3ng \xfd th\xec google s\u1ebd \u0111i\u1ec1u h\u01b0\u1edbng b\u1ea1n v\u1ec1 Yelp c\xf9ng v\u1edbi 1 `Authorization Code`. Yelp g\u1eedi `Authorization Code` cho `Authorization Server` c\u1ee7a google v\xe0 nh\u1eadn l\u1ea1i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c `accessToken`. Yelp s\u1ebd s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng `accessToken` n\xe0y v\xe0 g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn `Resource server` c\u1ee7a google \u0111\u1ec3 nh\u1eadn v\u1ec1 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c `resource` nh\u01b0 avatar ho\u1eb7c email,...\\n\\n## JWT\\n\\nTham kh\u1ea3o [\u1edf \u0111\xe2y](https://viblo.asia/p/tim-hieu-ve-json-web-token-jwt-7rVRqp73v4bP)"},{"id":"http-in-a-nutshell","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/http-in-a-nutshell","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-27-http-in-a-nutshell/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-27-http-in-a-nutshell/index.md","title":"Http in a nutshell","description":"_Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP)_ l\xe0 m\u1ed9t giao th\u1ee9c(protocol) thu\u1ed9c l\u1edbp \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf cho \u0111\u1ec3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n giao ti\u1ebfp gi\u1eefa web browsers v\xe0 web servers, nh\u01b0ng n\xf3 c\u0169ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng cho nhi\u1ec1u m\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch kh\xe1c. HTTP tu\xe2n theo m\xf4 h\xecnh client-server c\u1ed5 \u0111i\u1ec3n, v\u1edbi m\u1ed9t client open connection \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ea1o request, sau \u0111\xf3 ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c response. HTTP l\xe0 m\u1ed9t giao th\u1ee9c kh\xf4ng c\xf3 tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i, ngh\u0129a l\xe0 server kh\xf4ng d\u1eef tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i gi\u1eefa 2 l\u1ea7n requests.","date":"2021-08-27T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 27, 2021","tags":[{"label":"http","permalink":"/blog/tags/http"},{"label":"https","permalink":"/blog/tags/https"}],"readingTime":8.165,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Authentication in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/authentication-in-a-nutshell"},"nextItem":{"title":"Database indexing c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n","permalink":"/blog/database-indexing-basic"}},"content":"**_Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP)_** l\xe0 m\u1ed9t giao th\u1ee9c(protocol) thu\u1ed9c [l\u1edbp \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng](/blog/mang-may-tinh/) \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf cho \u0111\u1ec3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n giao ti\u1ebfp gi\u1eefa web browsers v\xe0 web servers, nh\u01b0ng n\xf3 c\u0169ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng cho nhi\u1ec1u m\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch kh\xe1c. HTTP tu\xe2n theo m\xf4 h\xecnh client-server c\u1ed5 \u0111i\u1ec3n, v\u1edbi m\u1ed9t client open connection \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ea1o request, sau \u0111\xf3 ch\u1edd cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c response. HTTP l\xe0 m\u1ed9t giao th\u1ee9c kh\xf4ng c\xf3 tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i, ngh\u0129a l\xe0 server kh\xf4ng d\u1eef tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i gi\u1eefa 2 l\u1ea7n requests.\\n\\n## HTTP Messages\\n\\nHTTP messages l\xe0 c\xe1ch m\xe0 data \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c trao \u0111\u1ed5i gi\u1eefa client v\xe0 server. C\xf3 2 lo\u1ea1i messages: requests g\u1eedi t\u1eeb client \u0111\u1ec3 trigger 1 action t\u1eeb server v\xe0 responses t\u1eeb server.\\n\\n![httpmsg2.png](/img/blogs/httpmsg2.png)\\nHTTP requests, responses c\xf3 c\u1ea5u tr\xfac t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 nhau:\\n\\n1. start-line mi\xeau ta requests \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 status c\u1ee7a response.\\n2. M\u1ed9t set HTTP headres ch\u1ec9 r\xf5 v\u1ec1 request ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 mi\xeau t\u1ea3 body c\u1ee7a response.\\n3. M\u1ed9t d\xf2ng tr\u1ed1ng ch\u1ec9 r\u1eb1ng t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 meta-info \u0111\u1ec1u \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi.\\n4. M\u1ed9t body ch\u1ee9a data c\u1ee7a request (ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 HTML form) ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 doc g\u1eedi theo response. K\xedch th\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0 lo\u1ea1i data m\xe0 ph\u1ea7n body ch\u1ee9a s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1ec9 r\xf5 \u1edf ph\u1ea7n headers.\\n   ![httpmsgstructure2.png](/img/blogs/httpmsgstructure2.png)\\n\\n## Content Security Policy (CSP)\\n\\n**Content Security Policy** l\xe0 m\u1ed9t l\u1edbp b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt gi\xfap ph\xe1t hi\u1ec7n v\xe0 gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u m\u1ed9t v\xe0i th\u1ec3 lo\u1ea1i t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng bao g\u1ed3m Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) v\xe0 Data Injection. Nh\u1eefng cu\u1ed9c t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng cho t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 m\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch t\u1eeb tr\u1ed9m d\u1eef li\u1ec7u cho \u0111\u1ebfn site defacement(thay \u0111\u1ed5i di\u1ec7n m\u1ea1o c\u1ee7a site) \u0111\u1ec3 ph\xe2n t\xe1n malware.\\n\\nCSP \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thi\u1ebft k\u1ebf \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 fully [backward compatibility](/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec/#backward-compatibility-l\xe0-g\xec-). Nh\u1eefng browsers m\xe0 kh\xf4ng h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 CSP th\xec v\u1eabn c\xf3 th\u1ec3 k\xedch ho\u1ea1t l\u1edbp b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt n\xe0y b\u1eb1ng server v\xe0 ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i. N\u1ebfu m\u1ed9t website kh\xf4ng cung c\u1ea5p CSP header th\xec browsers s\u1ebd s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng [same-origin policy](/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec/#same-origin-policy-l%C3%A0-g%C3%AC-).\\n\\n\u0110\u1ec3 k\xedch ho\u1ea1t CSP th\xec b\u1ea1n c\u1ea7n c\u1ea5u h\xecnh webserver tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1 Content-Security-Policy HTTP header. (Th\u1ec9nh tho\u1ea3ng b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd th\u1ea5y X-Content-Security-Policy header nh\u01b0ng \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 1 phi\xean b\u1ea3n c\u0169 c\u1ee7a CSP n\xean b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n quan t\xe2m \u0111\u1ebfn n\u1eefa).\\n\\nHo\u1eb7c b\u1ea1n c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 th\xeam th\u1ebb sau v\xe0o file html \u0111\u1ec3 k\xedch ho\u1ea1t CSP:\\n\\n```html\\n<meta\\n  http-equiv=\\"Content-Security-Policy\\"\\n  content=\\"default-src \'self\'; img-src https://*; child-src \'none\';\\"\\n/>\\n```\\n\\n### Threats\\n\\n1. Gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u XSS attacks.\\n   M\u1ee5c ti\xeau ch\xednh c\u1ee7a CSP l\xe0 gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u XSS attacks. XSS attacks l\u1ee3i d\u1ee5ng s\u1ef1 tin t\u01b0\u1edfng c\u1ee7a browser v\xe0o content nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1eeb server. C\xe1c \u0111o\u1ea1n scripts \u0111\u1ed9c c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi b\u1edfi browser c\u1ee7a n\u1ea1n nh\xe2n v\xec browser\u0111\xe3 tin t\u01b0\u1edfng v\xe0o ngu\u1ed3n c\u1ee7a content m\xecnh nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c, k\u1ec3 c\u1ea3 khi n\xf3 kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1eeb n\u01a1i m\xe0 n\xf3 \u0111\xe1ng l\u1ebd ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1eeb.\\n\\nCSP gi\xfap server admin gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u XSS b\u1eb1ng c\xe1ch ch\u1ec9 r\xf5 cho browser bi\u1ebft ch\u1ec9 n\xean tin t\u01b0\u1edfng v\xe0o nh\u1eefng domain c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3. Sau \u0111\xf3 th\xec khi browser nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c scripts th\xec n\xf3 s\u1ebd ch\u1ec9 th\u1ef1c thi nh\u1eefng scripts c\xf3 ngu\u1ed3n g\u1ed1c \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u1ecbnh t\u1eeb web server ho\u1eb7c t\u1eeb th\u1ebb meta \u1edf tr\xean v\xe0 b\u1ecf qua c\xe1c scripts kh\xe1c (k\u1ec3 c\u1ea3 inline scripts v\xe0 event-handling HTML attributes)\\n\\n2. Gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u packet sniffing attacks\\n   \u0110\u1ec3 gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u sniffing th\xec c\u1ea7n giao ti\u1ebfp qua HTTPS.\\n\\n### Directives\\n\\nTham kh\u1ea3o th\xeam [\u1edf \u0111\xe2y](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy)\\n\\n## Strict-Transport-Security\\n\\n**HTTP Strict-Transport-Security** response header l\xe0 m\u1ed9t header webserver tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1 v\xe0 n\xf3 n\xf3i v\u1edbi browser l\xe0 ch\u1ec9 truy c\u1eadp v\u1edbi giao th\u1ee9c HTTPS thay v\xec HTTP th\xf4ng th\u01b0\u1eddng.\\n\\nSyntax\\n\\n```nginx\\nStrict-Transport-Security: max-age=<expire-time>;\\nStrict-Transport-Security: max-age=<expire-time>; includeSubDomains;\\nStrict-Transport-Security: max-age=<expire-time>; preload\\n```\\n\\n- `expire-time` \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\xednh b\u1eb1ng gi\xe2y.\\n- `includeSubDomains` \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u1ecbnh th\xec nh\u1eefng quy t\u1eafc n\xe0y c\u0169ng \xe1p d\u1ee5ng v\u1edbi subdomains c\u1ee7a site.\\n- `preload` xem th\xeam \u1edf [\u0111\xe2y](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Strict-Transport-Security)\\n\\nN\u1ebfu m\u1ed9t site cho ph\xe9p connect qua HTTP v\xe0 sau \u0111\xf3 redirects t\u1edbi HTTPS th\xec ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi phi\xean b\u1ea3n ch\u01b0a \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c m\xe3 h\xf3a c\u1ee7a site tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c redirect, \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y t\u1ea1o c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i cho [man-in-the-middle](/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec/#man-in-the-middle-attack-l%C3%A0-g%C3%AC-) attack. Vi\u1ec7c redirect c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c khai th\xe1c \u0111\u1ec3 h\u01b0\u1edbng ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng \u0111\u1ebfn 1 site kh\xe1c thay v\xec b\u1ea3n b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt c\u1ee7a site g\u1ed1c.\\n\\nHSTS header n\xf3i v\u1edbi browsers r\u1eb1ng kh\xf4ng bao gi\u1edd truy c\u1eadp v\xe0o 1 site s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng giao th\u1ee9c HTTP m\xe0 n\xean t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng chuy\u1ec3n t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 qua HTTPS.\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5: B\u1ea1n s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Wifi mi\u1ec5n ph\xed \u1edf s\xe2n bay v\xe0 b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u truy c\u1eadp web. B\u1ea1n truy c\u1eadp d\u1ecbch v\u1ee5 ng\xe2n h\xe0ng \u0111\u1ec3 ki\u1ec3m tra t\xe0i kho\u1ea3n v\xe0 thanh to\xe1n 1 s\u1ed1 h\xf3a \u0111\u01a1n. Kh\xf4ng may r\u1eb1ng \u0111i\u1ec3m wifi mi\u1ec5n ph\xed \u0111\xf3 l\u1ea1i \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1eeb laptop c\u1ee7a hacker, v\xe0 hacker \u0111\xf3 ch\u1eb7n t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c HTTP request c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n v\xe0 chuy\u1ec3n h\u01b0\u1edbng v\u1ec1 1 trang kh\xe1c clone giao di\u1ec7n c\u1ee7a bank m\xe0 b\u1ea1n \u0111ang \u0111\u1ecbnh d\xf9ng. B\xe2y gi\u1edd b\u1ea1n nh\u1eadp t\xe0i kho\u1ea3n v\xe0 m\u1eadt kh\u1ea9u v\xe0o th\xec hacker s\u1ebd nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 th\xf4ng tin n\xe0y.\\n\\nHSTS gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 n\xe0y, m\u1ed9t khi b\u1ea1n \u0111\xe3 truy c\u1eadp v\xe0o trang web c\u1ee7a bank s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng HTTPS v\xe0 site \u0111\xf3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng HSTS th\xec browser c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd m\u1eb7c ch\u1ec9 giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi b\u1ea1n qua HTTPS ng\u0103n ch\u1eb7n hacker t\u1ea5n c\xf4ng man-in-the-middle.\\n\\n## S\u1eed d\u1ee5ng HTTP cookies\\n\\n**HTTP cookie** hay web cookie, browser cookie l\xe0 m\u1ed9t m\u1ea3nh data nh\u1ecf \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1eeb server \u0111\u1ebfn browser. Browser c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\u01b0u n\xf3 v\xe0 g\u1eedi l\u1ea1i c\xf9ng v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng request ti\u1ebfp theo cho browser. Ti\xeau bi\u1ec3u th\xec n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 server bi\u1ebft 2 requests \u0111\u1ebfn c\xf9ng 1 browser gi\u1eef cho user logged-in.\\n\\nCookies \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng cho 3 m\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch ch\xednh sau:\\n\\n- Qu\u1ea3n l\xfd session: Logins, Shopping carts, game scores hay b\u1ea5t c\u1ee9 th\u1ee9 g\xec m\xe0 server n\xean nh\u1edb.\\n- Personalization: M\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 preferences c\u1ee7a user, themes, c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t.\\n- Tracking: L\u01b0u tr\u1eef v\xe0 ph\xe2n t\xedch h\xe0nh vi ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng.\\n\\nCookies t\u1eebng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 l\u01b0u tr\u1eef chung ph\xeda client v\xe0 t\u1eebng l\xe0 c\xe1ch duy nh\u1ea5t, ng\xe0y nay th\xec l\u01b0u tr\u1eef ph\xeda client n\xean s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng c\xe1c APIs nh\u01b0 Web Storage API(localStorage v\xe0 sessionStorage) v\xe0 IndexedDB.\\n\\n### \u0110\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a lifetime cho 1 cookie\\n\\nC\xf3 2 c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a nh\u01b0 sau:\\n\\n- Session cookies \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c x\xf3a khi m\u1ed7i current session k\u1ebft th\xfac - \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c quy \u0111\u1ecbnh b\u1edfi browser, m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 browser s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng l\u01b0u tr\u1eef l\u1ea1i session khi restart browser, vi\u1ec7c n\xe0y c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m cho session cookies k\xe9o d\xe0i v\xf4 t\u1eadn.\\n- Permanent cookies \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c set ng\xe0y c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 cho vi\u1ec7c h\u1ebft h\u1ea1n, ho\u1eb7c c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c set 1 kho\u1ea3ng th\u1eddi gian h\u1ebft h\u1ea1n qua `Max-Age`.\\n\\nN\u1ebfu site c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n c\xf3 authenticates users, th\xec b\u1ea1n n\xean regenerate v\xe0 g\u1eedi l\u1ea1i session cookies m\u1ed7i khi user authenticates cho d\xf9 session cookies \u0111\xe3 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i. K\u1ef9 thu\u1eadt n\xe0y ng\u0103n ch\u1eb7n session fixation attacks, khi m\xe0 1 b\xean th\u1ee9 3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng l\u1ea1i session c\u1ee7a user.\\n\\n### H\u1ea1n ch\u1ebf truy c\u1eadp t\u1edbi cookies\\n\\nC\xf3 m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o cookies \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111i m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt v\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch kh\xf4ng ch\u1ee7 \xfd th\xf4ng qua thu\u1ed9c t\xednh `Secure` v\xe0 `HttpOnly`.\\n\\nM\u1ed9t cookie v\u1edbi thu\u1ed9c t\xednh `Secure` s\u1ebd ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ec3 sever khi \u0111ang k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i b\u1eb1ng HTTPS. C\xe1c site v\u1edbi http th\xec kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 set `Secure` cho cookie. Tuy nhi\xean `Secure` c\u0169ng kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o ch\u1eb7n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea5t c\xe1c c\xe1c truy c\u1eadp v\xe0o th\xf4ng tin nh\u1ea1y c\u1ea3m \u1edf cookie; v\xed d\u1ee5 n\xf3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ecdc d\u01b0\u1ee3c v\xe0 ch\u1ec9nh s\u1eeda b\u1edfi ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c n\u1ebfu h\u1ecd truy c\u1eadp \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c v\xe0o \u1ed5 c\u1ee9ng c\u1ee7a client ho\u1eb7c JS n\u1ebfu `HttpOnly` kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c set.\\n\\nM\u1ed9t cookie v\u1edbi thu\u1ed9c t\xednh `HttpOnly` th\xec kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c truy c\u1eadp b\u1eb1ng `Document.cookie` API; n\xf3 s\u1ebd ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn sever. V\xed d\u1ee5 v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng cookie m\xe0 gi\u1eef server-side sessions th\xec kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n truy c\u1eadp b\u1edfi JS, v\xe0 n\xean c\xf3 thu\u1ed9c t\xednh n\xe0y. N\xf3 gi\u1ea3m thi\u1ec3u XSS attacks.\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5:\\n\\n```javascript\\nSet-Cookie: id=a3fWa; Expires=Thu, 21 Oct 2021 07:28:00 GMT; Secure; HttpOnly\\n```\\n\\n## X-Content-Type-Options\\n\\n**X-Content-Type-Options** header l\xe0 m\u1ed9t HTTP header \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1eeb webserver nh\u01b0 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t c\xe1i mark \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 server ch\u1ec9 ra nh\u1eefng [MIME types](http://localhost:1313/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec/#mime-types-l%C3%A0-g%C3%AC-) b\xe1o trong Content-Type headers kh\xf4ng n\xean b\u1ecb thay \u0111\u1ed5i v\xe0 ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tu\xe2n theo. Hay n\xf3i c\xe1ch kh\xe1c MIME types \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5u h\xecnh m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch c\u1ea9n th\u1eadn.\\n\\nNh\u1eefng tester v\u1ec1 b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt s\u1ebd lu\xf4n mong mu\u1ed1n header n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c set.\\n\\nT\xecm hi\u1ec3u th\xeam [\u1edf \u0111\xe2y](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Content-Type-Options)\\n\\n## X-Frame-Options\\n\\n**X-Frame-Options** header l\xe0 m\u1ed9t HTTP header \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1eeb server \u0111\u1ec3 n\xf3i cho browser bi\u1ebft c\xf3 n\xean \u0111\u1ed3ng \xfd render m\u1ed9t page trong m\u1ed9t `frame`, `iframe`, `embed` ho\u1eb7c `object` hay kh\xf4ng. C\xe1c site c\xf3 th\u1ec3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng header n\xe0y \u0111\u1ec3 tr\xe1nh [click-jacking](http://localhost:1313/blog/mot-so-thuat-ngu-pho-bien-ma-minh-gap-xuyen-suot-hoc-tap-va-lam-viec/#click-jacking-attack-l%C3%A0-g%C3%AC-) attacks, b\u1eb1ng c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o r\u1eb1ng content c\u1ee7a site kh\xf4ng b\u1ecb nh\xfang v\xe0o nh\u1eefng sites kh\xe1c.\\n\\nL\u1edbp b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt n\xe0y ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\xeam v\xe0o khi browser c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 `X-Frame-Options`\\n\\n**Syntax**\\n\\n```nginx\\nX-Frame-Options: DENY\\nX-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN\\n```\\n\\n- DENY: page kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 hi\u1ec3n th\u1ecb trong 1 frame\\n- SAMEORIGIN: page ch\u1ec9 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c hi\u1ec3n th\u1ecb trong 1 frame c\xf3 c\xf9ng origin v\u1edbi page.\\n- ALLOW-FROM uri: kh\xf4ng c\xf2n ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng \u1edf tr\xean browsers m\u1edbi. Kh\xf4ng n\xean s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng.\\n\\n**Config tr\xean Nginx**\\n\\n```nginx\\nadd_header X-Frame-Options SAMEORIGIN always;\\n```\\n\\n**Config tr\xean Express**\\n\\n```javascript\\nconst helmet = require(\\"helmet\\");\\nconst app = express();\\napp.use(helmet.frameguard({ action: \\"SAMEORIGIN\\" }));\\n```\\n\\n## X-XSS-Protection\\n\\n**X-Frame-Options** header l\xe0 m\u1ed9t HTTP header \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1eeb server, \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 m\u1ed9t header \u0111\u1ec3 k\xedch ho\u1ea1t t\xednh n\u0103ng b\u1ea3o v\u1ec7 XSS attacks tr\xean nh\u1eefng tr\xecnh duy\u1ec7t nh\u01b0 IE, Chrome, Safari ng\u0103n vi\u1ec7c load nh\u1eefng page m\xe0 browser ph\xe1t hi\u1ec7n kh\u1ea3 n\u0103ng c\xf3 XSS attacks. M\u1eb7c d\xf9 t\xednh n\u0103ng n\xe0y l\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n thi\u1ebft v\xec h\u1ea7u h\u1ebft c\xe1c site c\xf3 th\u1ec3 implement CSP nh\u1eefng v\u1eabn c\xf3 th\u1ec3 h\u1eefu \xedch \u0111\u1ed1i v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng browser c\u0169 ch\u01b0a h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 CSP.\\n\\n**Note**:\\n\\n- Chrome \u0111\xe3 lo\u1ea1i b\u1ecf XSS Auditor\\n- Firefox s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng implement t\xednh n\u0103ng n\xe0y.\\n- Edge c\u0169ng lo\u1ea1i b\u1ecf XSS filter."},{"id":"database-indexing-basic","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/database-indexing-basic","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-26-database-indexing-basic/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-26-database-indexing-basic/index.md","title":"Database indexing c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n","description":"Nh\u1eefng ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y s\u1ebd \xe1p d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c v\u1edbi postgres c\xf2n nh\u1eefng database kh\xe1c th\xec m\xecnh kh\xf4ng ch\u1eafc nh\xe9.","date":"2021-08-26T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 26, 2021","tags":[{"label":"database","permalink":"/blog/tags/database"},{"label":"indexing","permalink":"/blog/tags/indexing"}],"readingTime":4.46,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Http in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/http-in-a-nutshell"},"nextItem":{"title":"Transaction in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/transaction-in-a-nutshell"}},"content":"Nh\u1eefng ki\u1ebfn th\u1ee9c d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y s\u1ebd \xe1p d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c v\u1edbi postgres c\xf2n nh\u1eefng database kh\xe1c th\xec m\xecnh kh\xf4ng ch\u1eafc nh\xe9.\\n\\n## Row \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o ?\\n\\n![heap-storage-structure](/img/blogs/basic-heap-storage-structure.png)\\n\\nC\u1ea5u tr\xfac \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 l\u01b0u tr\u1eef 1 `table` l\xe0 1 heap file - list c\xe1c `page` c\xf3 fixed size (th\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0 8Kb). Trong 1 `table` th\xec t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c `page` \u0111\u1ec1u t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u01b0\u01a1ng v\u1ec1 m\u1eb7t logic, n\xean 1 `row` c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u tr\u1eef \u1edf b\u1ea5t k\u1ef3 page n\xe0o.\\n\\nC\u1ea5u tr\xfac c\u1ee7a 1 page c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 nh\u01b0 sau:\\n![heap-file-page](/img/blogs/heap_file_page.png)\\n\\n- 1 Page th\xec c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u headers, ch\xfang bao g\u1ed3m checksum, start of free space, end of free space.\\n- Sau headers l\xe0 1 list c\xe1c identifier bao g\u1ed3m offset, length v\xe0 tr\u1ecf \u0111\u1ebfn 1 item(row).\\n- 1 Pointer \u0111\u1ebfn 1 item th\xec \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 CTID v\xe0 b\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 truy c\u1eadp CTID b\u1eb1ng c\xe1ch: `select ctid, * from users;`\\n- C\xe1c identifier th\xec \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u \u1edf \u0111\u1ea7u page tr\u1edf xu\u1ed1ng.\\n- Tuple \u1edf \u0111\xe2y ch\xednh l\xe0 1 row trong table, c\xe1c row th\xec l\u1ea1i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i t\u1eeb d\u01b0\u1edbi l\xean.\\n\\n## T\u1ea1i sao c\u1ea7n indexing ?\\n\\nV\u1eady l\xe0 ch\xfang ta \u0111\xe3 bi\u1ebft \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c row \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c gom th\xe0nh c\xe1c page(block) n\u1ed1i ti\u1ebfp nhau trong file heap. B\xe2y gi\u1edd s\u1ebd nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o n\u1ebfu ta t\xecm ki\u1ebfm nh\u1eefng row c\xf3 1 tr\u01b0\u1eddng c\xf3 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 ?\\n\\n\u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng tr\u01b0\u1eddng kh\xf4ng unique th\xec khi search tr\xean tr\u01b0\u1eddng \u1ea5y ch\xfang ta ph\u1ea3i search tr\xean to\xe0n b\u1ed9(N) c\xe1c block, \u0111\u1ed1i v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng tr\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0 key (unique) th\xec c\xf3 th\u1ec3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng Linear Search v\xe0 y\xeau c\u1ea7u trung b\xecnh truy xu\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ebfn (N+1)/2 blocks.\\n\\n\u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng tr\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c sorted s\u1eb5n v\xe0 unique th\xec l\xfac \u0111\u1ea5y c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \xe1p d\u1ee5ng Binary Search v\xe0 b\xe2y gi\u1edd th\xec s\u1ed1 l\u01b0\u1ee3ng blocks c\u1ea7n truy xu\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ebfn gi\u1ea3m xu\u1ed1ng ch\u1ec9 c\xf2n log2(N). \u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi N l\u1edbn th\xec performance s\u1ebd t\u0103ng l\xean \u0111\xe1ng k\u1ec3. V\xe0 \u0111\xe2y c\u0169ng ch\xednh l\xe0 l\xfd do m\xe0 ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng indexing.\\n\\n## Indexing l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\nKhi t\u1ea1o 1 index th\xec 1 file m\u1edbi s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o ra v\xe0 c\xf3 shema nh\u01b0 sau.\\n\\nSchema c\u1ee7a m\u1ed9t index:\\n\\n```postgres\\nField name       Data type      Size on disk\\nfirstName        Char(50)       50 bytes\\n(record pointer) Special        4 bytes\\n```\\n\\nSau khi t\u1ea1o ra index n\xe0y th\xec n\xf3 s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c sorted \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \xe1p d\u1ee5ng Binary Searches. Vi\u1ec7c t\u1ea1o ra nhi\u1ec1u index kh\xf4ng h\u1ee3p l\xfd s\u1ebd d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn vi\u1ec7c ti\xeau t\u1ed1n b\u1ed9 nh\u1edb \u1ed5 \u0111\u0129a kh\xf4ng c\u1ea7n thi\u1ebft.\\n\\n## Index ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o ?\\n\\nGi\u1ea3 s\u1eed ch\xfang ta c\xf3 1 table c\xf3 5,000,000 rows t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 nh\u01b0 n\xe0y:\\n\\n```postgres\\nField name       Data type      Size on disk\\nid (Primary key) Unsigned INT   4 bytes\\nfirstName        Char(50)       50 bytes\\nlastName         Char(50)       50 bytes\\nemailAddress     Char(100)      100 bytes\\n```\\n\\nTa th\u1ea5y th\xec m\u1ed7i row \u1edf \u0111\xe2y s\u1ebd c\xf3 fixed size l\xe0 `204 bytes`, \u1edf \u0111\xe2y ta s\u1ebd s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng postgres c\xf3 size cho m\u1ed7i block(page) l\xe0 8Kb = `8192 bytes` v\u1eady m\u1ed7i block s\u1ebd c\xf3 ~ 40 rows, m\xecnh s\u1ebd t\u1ea1m th\u1eddi b\u1ecf qua headers c\u0169ng nh\u01b0 CTID v\xe0 c\xe1c th\xe0nh ph\u1ea7n kh\xe1c.\\n\\n**Note**: \u1ede \u0111\xe2y th\xec char \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng thay cho varchar \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o size on disk fixed v\xe0 thu\u1eadn ti\u1ec7n cho vi\u1ec7c t\xednh to\xe1n d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y.\\n\\nV\u1edbi 5,000,000 rows th\xec ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd c\xf3 kho\u1ea3ng N = 5,000,000 / 40 = 125,000 blocks. N\u1ebfu query tr\u01b0\u1eddng firstname th\xec ta s\u1ebd ph\u1ea3i query to\xe0n b\u1ed9 125,000 blocks, c\xf2n v\u1edbi tr\u01b0\u1eddng id \u0111\xe3 unique v\xe0 sorted s\u1eb5n n\xean s\u1ed1 blocks truy xu\u1ea5t ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 ~17 blocks.\\n\\nN\u1ebfu ta t\u1ea1o index cho tr\u01b0\u1eddng firstname v\u1eady m\u1ed7i row s\u1ebd c\xf3 size l\xe0 `54 bytes`, m\u1ed7i block `8192 bytes` v\u1eady s\u1ebd c\xf3 8192/54 ~ 150 rows trong m\u1ed7i block v\u1eady N = 5,000,000 / 150 = 33,333 blocks. \u0110\u1ec3 truy xu\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ebfn 1 row c\xf3 firstname b\u1eb1ng 1 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ecbnh th\xec l\xfac n\xe0y ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd ch\u1ec9 c\xf2n c\u1ea7n query ~ 15 + 1 = 16 blocks gi\u1ea3m 1 s\u1ed1 l\u01b0\u1ee3ng kinh kh\u1ee7ng so v\u1edbi tr\u01b0\u1edbc. +1 \xe1m ch\u1ec9 r\u1eb1ng sau khi l\u1ea5y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c record pointer th\xec ta s\u1ebd c\u1ea7n query \u0111\u1ebfn heap \u0111\u1ec3 l\u1ea5y d\u1eef li\u1ec7u kh\xe1c nh\u01b0 lastname, emailAddress.\\n\\n## Create Postgres Table with a moillion Rows (from scratch)\\n\\n```postgres\\ncreate table temp(t int);\\ninsert into temp(t) select random()*100 from generate_series(0, 1000000);\\nselect count(*) from temp;\\n```\\n\\n## Using Explain\\n\\n![pg-explain-1](/img/blogs/pg-explain-1.png)\\n\\n- Seq Scan c\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 n\xf3 s\u1ebd full-table scan (s\u1ebd t\xecm \u0111\u1ebfn heap v\xe0 fetch t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 \u0111\u1ec3 scan).\\n- Cost th\u01b0\u1eddng c\xf3 2 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb: gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb \u0111\u1ea7u l\xe0 s\u1ed1 milisecond \u0111\u1ec3 pg fetch page \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean c\u1ee7a table, n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n hay pg kh\xf4ng y\xeau c\u1ea7u vi\u1ec7c g\xec (nh\u01b0 ordering ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n) th\xec vi\u1ec7c n\xe0y s\u1ebd t\u1ed1n r\u1ea5t \xedt th\u1eddi gian, n\u1ebfu s\u1ed1 n\xe0y t\u0103ng cao th\xec ngh\u0129a pg \u0111ang l\xe0m r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u th\u1ee9 kh\xe1c tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi fetching. Gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb th\u1ee9 2 l\xe0 th\u1eddi gian m\xe0 pg suy ngh\u0129 c\xe1c vi\u1ec7c s\u1ebd l\xe0m.\\n- Rows l\xe0 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb estimate m\xe0 query tr\u1ea3 v\u1ec1.\\n- Width l\xe0 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb b\u1eb1ng bytes c\u1ee7a m\u1ed7i row.\\n\\nB\xe0i n\xe0y m\xecnh xin ph\xe9p d\u1eebng t\u1ea1i \u0111\xe2y v\xec c\u0169ng kh\xe1 d\xe0i r\u1ed3i, m\xecnh s\u1ebd ti\u1ebfp t\u1ee5c c\u1eadp nh\u1eadt c\xe1c b\xe0i vi\u1ebft kh\xe1c trong chu\u1ed7i b\xe0i v\u1ec1 postgres.\\n\\n## Tham kh\u1ea3o\\n\\n- [Introduction to PostgreSQL physical storage](http://rachbelaid.com/introduction-to-postgres-physical-storage/)\\n- [How does database indexing work](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1108/how-does-database-indexing-work)"},{"id":"transaction-in-a-nutshell","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/transaction-in-a-nutshell","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-25-transaction-in-a-nutshell/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-25-transaction-in-a-nutshell/index.md","title":"Transaction in a nutshell","description":"Transaction c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a l\xe0 1 nh\xf3m task. M\u1ed9t task \u0111\u01a1n l\u1ebb l\xe0 1 \u0111\u01a1n v\u1ecb x\u1eed l\xfd m\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 chia nh\u1ecf h\u01a1n n\u1eefa.","date":"2021-08-25T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 25, 2021","tags":[{"label":"acid","permalink":"/blog/tags/acid"},{"label":"database","permalink":"/blog/tags/database"},{"label":"transaction","permalink":"/blog/tags/transaction"}],"readingTime":6.05,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Database indexing c\u01a1 b\u1ea3n","permalink":"/blog/database-indexing-basic"},"nextItem":{"title":"ACID trong c\u01a1 s\u1edf d\u1eef li\u1ec7u","permalink":"/blog/acid-trong-co-so-du-lieu"}},"content":"_Transaction c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a l\xe0 1 nh\xf3m task. M\u1ed9t task \u0111\u01a1n l\u1ebb l\xe0 1 \u0111\u01a1n v\u1ecb x\u1eed l\xfd m\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 chia nh\u1ecf h\u01a1n n\u1eefa._\\n\\n_L\u1ea5y m\u1ed9t v\xed d\u1ee5 \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n. Gi\u1ea3 s\u1eed m\u1ed9t nh\xe2n vi\xean ng\xe2n h\xe0ng chuy\u1ec3n 500 tri\u1ec7u t\u1eeb t\xe0i kho\u1ea3n A \u0111\u1ebfn t\xe0i kho\u1ea3n B. \u0110\xe2y l\xe0 m\u1ed9t transaction \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n ch\u1ee9a nh\u1eefng task sau \u0111\xe2y._\\n\\n**A\'s Account**\\n\\n```sh\\nOpen_Account(A)\\nOld_Balance = A.balance\\nNew_Balance = Old_Balance - 500\\nA.balance = New_Balance\\nClose_Account(A)\\n```\\n\\n**B\'s Account**\\n\\n```sh\\nOpen_Account(B)\\nOld_Balance = B.balance\\nNew_Balance = Old_Balance + 500\\nB.balance = New_Balance\\nClose_Account(B)\\n```\\n\\nM\u1ed9t transaction ph\u1ea3i duy tr\xec \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\xe1c thu\u1ed9c t\xednh [ACID](/blog/acid-trong-co-so-du-lieu/) \u0111\u1ec3m \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o \u0111\u1ed9 ch\xednh x\xe1c, t\xednh nguy\xean v\u1eb9n c\u1ee7a database.\\n\\n## 1. States c\u1ee7a Transactions\\n\\n![state-of-transaction](/img/blogs/transaction_states.png)\\n\\n- **Active**: Transaction b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi, \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i kh\u1edfi \u0111\u1ea7u c\u1ee7a t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c transcation.\\n- **Partially Committed**: M\u1ed9t transaction s\u1ebd th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n nhi\u1ec1u task, v\xe0 khi task cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n th\xec transaction s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c xem l\xe0 \u1edf tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i n\xe0y.\\n- **Failed**: B\u1ea5t c\u1ee9 ki\u1ec3m tra n\xe0o t\u1eeb database b\u1ecb b\xe1o l\u1ed7i th\xec transaction s\u1ebd \u1edf tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i n\xe0y v\xe0 s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c x\u1eed l\xfd ti\u1ebfp.\\n- **Aborted**: Khi transaction \u0111\u1ea1t tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i failed th\xec database s\u1ebd rolls back l\u1ea1i t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 nh\u1eefng task th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c ghi d\u1eef li\u1ec7u, \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0a database \u0111\u1ea1t l\u1ea1i tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi transaction \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 re-start l\u1ea1i transaction.\\n- **Committed**: N\u1ebfu t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c task c\u1ee7a transaction \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n th\xe0nh c\xf4ng th\xec transaction \u0111\u1ea1t tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i n\xe0y, v\xe0 nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i \u0111\u1ebfn database s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u01b0u v\u0129nh vi\u1ec5n.\\n\\n## 2. Schedules l\xe0 g\xec ?\\n\\n![types-of-schedule](/img/blogs/Types-of-Schedules-in-DBMS.png)\\n\\n- **Schedule**: L\xe0 m\u1ed9t chu\u1ed7i n\u1ed1i ti\u1ebfp c\xe1c transaction, m\u1ed7i transaction th\xec c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u tasks.\\n- **Serial Schedule**: C\xe1c transaction trong schedule \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eafp x\u1ebfp c\xf3 tr\xecnh t\u1ef1, \u0111\u1ec3 khi 1 transaction ho\xe0n th\xe0nh v\xf2ng \u0111\u1eddi c\u1ee7a n\xf3 th\xec transaction ti\u1ebfp theo m\u1edbi \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi. Schedule ki\u1ec3u n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 schedule tu\u1ea7n t\u1ef1(serial schedule), v\xec c\xe1c transaction trong serial schedule \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi 1 c\xe1ch c\xf3 tu\u1ea7n t\u1ef1.\\n- **Non-Serial Schedules**: Nhi\u1ec1u transaction x\u1ea3y ra \u0111\u1ed3ng th\u1eddi. v\xe0 c\xe1c operations c\u1ee7a transactions th\xec c\xf3 t\xe1c \u0111\u1ed9ng \u0111\u1ebfn nhau.\\n\\nC\xe1c serial schedules th\xec c\xf3 c\xe1c \u0111\u1eb7c t\xednh nh\u01b0: consistent, recoverable, cascadeless(kh\xf4ng x\u1ebfp t\u1ea7ng, ch\u1ed3ng ch\u1ea5t l\xean nhau), strict.\\n\\nC\xf2n non-serial schedule th\xec kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i bao gi\u1edd c\u0169ng \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c nh\u1eefng t\xednh ch\u1ea5t nh\u01b0 v\u1eady.\\n\\n\u2753**Serial schedule \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o nh\u01b0 v\u1eady, t\u1ea1i sao ch\xfang ta l\u1ea1i c\u1ea7n non-serial schedule.**\\n\\nD\u1ec5 hi\u1ec3u khi trong serial schedule th\xec c\xe1c transaction \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n t\u1eebng c\xe1i 1 theo tr\xecnh t\u1ef1, T1 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh \xf2ng \u0111\u1eddi xong r\u1ed3i m\u1edbi \u0111\u1ebfn T2 n\xean r\u1ea5t l\xe0 ch\u1eadm, c\xf2n v\u1edbi non-serial schedule th\xec c\xe1c transaction x\u1ea3y ra song song n\xean r\u1ea5t nhanh, nh\u01b0ng c\u0169ng v\xec \u0111\xf3 m\xe0 kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c nh\u1eefng t\xednh ch\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c cho database lu\xf4n \u0111\xfang, v\u1eady n\xean nh\u1eefng method lo\u1ea1i b\u1ecf c\xe1c v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 v\u1ec1 concurrency \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o n\xean nh\u01b0 tr\xean.\\n\\n## 3. Serializability\\n\\nNh\u01b0 \u1edf tr\xean ch\xfang ta \u0111\xe3 n\xf3i th\xec ch\xfang ta mu\u1ed1n ch\u1ea1y c\xe1c transactions \u0111\u1ed3ng th\u1eddi (concurrency) v\xe0 c\u0169ng mu\u1ed1n c\xe1c k\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 sau khi th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n c\xe1c transactions n\xe0y gi\u1ed1ng v\u1edbi c\xe1ch c\u1ee7a serial schedule. Ta g\u1ecdi \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y l\xe0 `Serializability`\\n\\n![serializability-hierarchical](/img/blogs/Schedule-serializability.png)\\n\\n\u0110\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c serializability th\xec schedules c\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 equivalences d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y.\\n\\n## 4. Equivalence Schedules - C\xe1c t\xednh ch\u1ea5t t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u01b0\u01a1ng gi\u1eefa schedules\\n\\n2 schedules c\xf3 th\u1ec3 t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u01b0\u01a1ng v\u1ec1 m\u1eb7t result, view, conflict.\\n\\n**1. Result Equivalence**\\n![serial-schedule](/img/blogs/Equivalence-of-Schedules-Problem-01.png)\\nN\u1ebfu 2 schedules \u0111\u1ec1u cho k\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 gi\u1ed1ng nhau sau khi \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi th\xec ch\xfang \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c xem l\xe0 `result equivalence`. Ch\xfang c\xf3 th\u1ec3 cho result gi\u1ed1ng nhau \u1edf 1 v\xe0i gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb nh\u01b0ng c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 kh\xe1c nhau \u1edf 1 v\xe0i gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb kh\xe1c. V\xec th\u1ebf m\xe0 lo\u1ea1i n\xe0y kh\xf4ng c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u \xfd ngh\u0129a.\\n\\n\u1ede h\xecnh tr\xean l\u1ea5y X = 2 v\xe0 Y = 5\\n\\n- K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 c\u1ee7a S1: X = 21 v\xe0 Y = 10\\n- K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 c\u1ee7a S2: X = 21 v\xe0 Y = 10\\n- K\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 c\u1ee7a S3: X = 11 v\xe0 Y = 10\\n\\n\u2714\ufe0f V\u1eady S1 v\xe0 S2 result equivalence.\\n\\n**2. Conflict equivalent**\\n![conflice-equivalent](/img/blogs/Equivalence-of-Schedules-Problem-02.png)\\nN\u1ebfu 2 schedules th\u1ecfa m\xe3n 2 \u0111i\u1ec1u ki\u1ec7n d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y th\xec ch\xfang confict equivalent.\\n\\n- C\xe1c transcation \u1edf 2 schedules l\xe0 gi\u1ed1ng nhau.\\n- Tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 c\xe1c c\u1eb7p task confict \u1edf 2 schedules l\xe0 gi\xf3ng nhau.\\n\\nNh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o l\xe0 1 c\u1eb7p task conflict ?\\n\\nC\xe1c c\u1eb7p task conflict l\xe0 c\u1eb7p task x\u1ea3y ra tr\xean 2 transaction c\xf9ng truy xu\u1ea5t v\xe0 update \u0111\u1ebfn 1 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb c\u1ee7a database. V\xed d\u1ee5 nh\u01b0 l\xe0 T1 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n Read(X) v\xe0 T2 l\u1ea1i th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n Write(X) khi\u1ebfn gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb c\u1ee7a X l\xfac n\xe0y \u1edf 2 transaction l\xe0 kh\xe1c nhau. C\xf3 c\xe1c c\u1eb7p conflict nh\u01b0 sau: R1(X) W2(X); W1(X) R2(X) v\xe0 W1(X) W2(X).\\n\\nQuay l\u1ea1i \u1edf v\xed d\u1ee5 tr\xean th\xec \u0111\u1ed1i v\u1edbi S1 th\xec 2 transaction ch\u1ec9 c\xf9ng truy xu\u1ea5t v\xe0 update d\u1eef li\u1ec7u c\u1ee7a A, S2 c\u0169ng v\u1eady.\\n\\n\u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi S1 th\xec tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 c\xe1c c\u1eb7p conflict nh\u01b0 sau:\\n\\n- R1(A), W2(A)\\n- W1(A), R2(A)\\n- W1(A), W2(A)\\n\\n\u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi S2 th\xec tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 c\xe1c c\u1eb7p conflict nh\u01b0 sau:\\n\\n- R1(A), W2(A)\\n- W1(A), R2(A)\\n- W1(A), W2(A)\\n\\nV\u1eady \u1edf \u0111\xe2y ta c\xf3 n\xf3i S1 v\xe0 S2 l\xe0 c\xe1c conflict\\nequivalent schedules.\\n\\n**3. View Equivalence**\\n2 schedules c\xf3 view equivalence khi \u0111\xe1p \u1ee9ng 3 y\xeau c\u1ea7u sau:\\n\\n- V\u1edbi m\u1ed7i data item X, n\u1ebfu transaction Ti reads X t\u1eeb tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean \u1edf S1, sau \u0111\xf3 \u1edf S2, Ti c\u0169ng ph\u1ea3i reads X t\u1eeb tr\u1ea1ng th\xe1i \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean. Ngh\u0129a l\xe0 l\xfac Ti \u1edf S1 v\xe0 S2 read X th\xec ch\xfang ph\u1ea3i c\xf3 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb nh\u01b0 nhau.\\n- N\u1ebfu transaction Ti reads 1 data item m\xe0 \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c update b\u1edfi 1 transaction Tj \u1edf S1, th\xec \u1edf S2 transaction Ti c\u0169ng ph\u1ea3i reads \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u01b0\u01a1ng sau khi \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c update b\u1edfi 1 Tj kh\xe1c trong S2.\\n- V\u1edbi m\u1ed7i data item X, n\u1ebfu X \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c update b\u1edfi \xedt nh\u1ea5t 1 transaction Ti trong S1 th\xec \u1edf S2 n\xf3 c\u0169ng ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c update b\u1edfi \xedt nh\u1ea5t 1 transaction Ti trong S2.\\n\\nC\xe1c ph\u01b0\u01a1ng ph\xe1p \u0111\u1ec3 ki\u1ec3m tra xem 1 Schedule c\xf3 View Serializable hay kh\xf4ng ?\\n\\n1. Ki\u1ec3m tra xem schedule c\xf3 conflict serializable hay kh\xf4ng ?\\n\\n- N\u1ebfu 1 schedule l\xe0 conflict serializable th\xec ch\u1eafc ch\u1eafn n\xf3 view serializable.\\n- N\u1ebfu 1 schedule kh\xf4ng conflict serializable th\xec n\xf3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ho\u1eb7c kh\xf4ng view serializable, v\xe0 ki\u1ec3m tra ti\u1ebfp theo b\u01b0\u1edbc d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y.\\n\\n2. Ki\u1ec3m tra xem schedule c\xf3 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i nh\u1eefng blind write operation hay kh\xf4ng?\\n   Blind write operation l\xe0 nh\u1eefng task th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c ghi m\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c \u0111\u1ecdc tr\u01b0\u1edbc \u0111\xf3.\\n\\n- N\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i, th\xec ch\u1eafc ch\u1eafn kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i view serializable.\\n- N\u1ebfu c\xf3 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i, th\xec ki\u1ec3m tra theo b\u01b0\u1edbc d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y.\\n\\n3. D\xf9ng nh\u1eefng y\xeau c\u1ea7u \u0111\xe3 n\xeau \u1edf tr\xean, vi\u1ebft l\u1ea1i t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c dependencies, v\u1ebd graph, n\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng c\xf3 v\xf2ng l\u1eb7p n\xe0o trong graph th\xec schedule \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 view serializable v\xe0 ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i.\\n\\n## 4. M\xecnh hay d\xf9ng postgres, v\u1eady postgres th\xec serializability nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o ?\\n\\nC\xe2u n\xe0y m\xecnh ngh\u0129 s\u1ebd t\xecm hi\u1ec3u v\xe0 tr\u1ea3 l\u1eddi trong 1 b\xe0i ri\xeang v\u1ec1 postgres \ud83d\ude04"},{"id":"acid-trong-co-so-du-lieu","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/acid-trong-co-so-du-lieu","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-24-acid-trong-database/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-24-acid-trong-database/index.md","title":"ACID trong c\u01a1 s\u1edf d\u1eef li\u1ec7u","description":"Transaction l\xe0 m\u1ed9t \u0111\u01a1n v\u1ecb logic n\xf3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c truy xu\u1ea5t v\xe0 ch\u1ec9nh s\u1eeda n\u1ed9i dung c\u1ee7a database. \u0110\u1ec3 duy tr\xec t\xednh th\u1ed1ng nh\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 database tr\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0 sau khi th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n transaction th\xec c\u1ea7n tu\xe2n theo m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 t\xednh ch\u1ea5t v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c vi\u1ebft t\u1eaft l\xe0 ACID","date":"2021-08-24T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 24, 2021","tags":[{"label":"acid","permalink":"/blog/tags/acid"},{"label":"database","permalink":"/blog/tags/database"}],"readingTime":4.885,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Transaction in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/transaction-in-a-nutshell"},"nextItem":{"title":"Snap in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/snap-in-a-nutshell"}},"content":"**Transaction l\xe0 m\u1ed9t \u0111\u01a1n v\u1ecb logic n\xf3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c truy xu\u1ea5t v\xe0 ch\u1ec9nh s\u1eeda n\u1ed9i dung c\u1ee7a database. \u0110\u1ec3 duy tr\xec t\xednh th\u1ed1ng nh\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 database tr\u01b0\u1edbc v\xe0 sau khi th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n transaction th\xec c\u1ea7n tu\xe2n theo m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 t\xednh ch\u1ea5t v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c vi\u1ebft t\u1eaft l\xe0 ACID**\\n\\n## Atomicity (/\xe6t.\u0259\u02c8m\u026as.\u026a.ti/)\\n\\nY\xeau c\u1ea7u transaction ph\u1ea3i th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n 1 c\xe1ch ho\xe0n ch\u1ec9nh ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n, ch\u1ee9 kh\xf4ng c\xf3 vi\u1ec7c ch\u1ec9 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n 1 ph\u1ea7n.\\n\\nN\xf3 li\xean quan \u0111\u1ebfn 2 th\u1ee9:\\n\\n- **Abort**: N\u1ebfu 1 transaction b\u1ecb h\u1ee7y b\u1ecf th\xec nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng c\xf2n n\u1eefa.\\n- **Commit**: N\u1ebfu 1 transaction \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c commit th\xec nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ghi l\u1ea1i.\\n\\n2 t\xednh ch\u1ea5t n\xe0y n\xf3 li\xean quan ch\u1eb7t ch\u1ebd \u0111\u1ebfn nhau.\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5 b\u1ea1n c\xf3 2 table: `product_templates` v\xe0 `products` v\u1edbi relation l\xe0 `One-To-Many` 1 product template c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u products con. product_template c\xf3 1 tr\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0 `min_price` l\xe0 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb th\u1ea5p nh\u1ea5t trong t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c `price` l\xe0 thu\u1ed9c t\xednh c\u1ee7a products.\\n\\nTa th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n 1 transaction th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n 2 vi\u1ec7c l\xe0 `delete product` v\xe0 `update min_price`. N\u1ebfu transaction \u0111\xf3 sau khi th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c delete product v\xe0 b\u1ecb l\u1ed7i th\xec data s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng c\xf2n \u0111\xfang n\u1eefa.\\n\\n## Isolation\\n\\nThu\u1ed9c t\xednh n\xe0y \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o r\u1eb1ng c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u transaction c\xf3 th\u1ec3 th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ed3ng th\u1eddi m\xe0 kh\xf4ng d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn database kh\xf4ng c\xf2n nh\u1ea5t qu\xe1n. C\xe1c transactions ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi m\u1ed9t c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ed9c l\u1eadp m\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\xf3 b\u1ea5t c\u1ee9 s\u1ef1 can thi\u1ec7p n\xe0o. Nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i t\u1eeb 1 transaction th\xec s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ea5y \u1edf c\xe1c transcations kh\xe1c cho \u0111\u1ebfn khi nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i \u1ea5y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ghi v\xe0o b\u1ed9 nh\u1edb ho\u1eb7c \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c commited.\\n\\nV\xed d\u1ee5: ta c\xf3 X = 10, Y = 5 v\xe0 2 transaction T v\xe0 T\'\\n\\n|     T     |    T\'    |\\n| :-------: | :------: |\\n|  Read(X)  | Read(X)  |\\n| X:= X\\\\*10 | Read(Y)  |\\n| Write(X)  |  Z:=X+Y  |\\n|  Read(Y)  | Write(Z) |\\n|  Y:=Y-2   |\\n\\n|Write(Y)\\n\\n\u1ede v\xed d\u1ee5 tr\xean n\u1ebfu transaction T th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n xong b\u01b0\u1edbc Write(X) v\xe0 transaction T\' b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u, n\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o t\xednh c\xf4 l\u1eadp c\u1ee7a c\xe1c transaction th\xec X \u1edf T\' s\u1ebd c\xf3 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb l\xe0 100 d\u1eabn t\u1edbi Z = 100 + 5 = 105. Tr\u01b0\u1eddng h\u1ee3p T kh\xf4ng commit m\xe0 rollback th\xec s\u1ebd d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn X quay l\u1ea1i l\xe0 10 v\xe0 Z s\u1ebd sai.\\n\\n1. Can my inflight transaction see changes made by other transactions ?\\n   \u0110i\u1ec1u n\xe0y c\xf2n t\xf9y thu\u1ed9c v\xe0o developer, ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 v\xed d\u1ee5 \u1edf tr\xean n\u1ebfu kh\xf4ng c\xf3 isolation n\xe0o th\xec T\' s\u1ebd Read(X) v\u1edbi gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb kh\xf4ng mong mu\u1ed1n.\\n2. Read phenomena: khi thi\u1ebfu isolation nh\u01b0 v\xed d\u1ee5 \u1edf tr\xean th\xec s\u1ebd d\u1eabn t\u1edbi vi\u1ec7c Read 1 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb n\xe0o \u0111\u1ea5y kh\xf4ng \u0111\xfang n\u1eefa.\\n3. Isolation Levels: \u0110\u1ec3 tr\xe1nh Read phenomena th\xec ta s\u1ebd th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n isolation cho transaction.\\n\\n### Read phenomena\\n\\n- Dirty reads: gi\u1ed1ng nh\u01b0 v\xed d\u1ee5 \u0111\xe3 n\xeau \u1edf tr\xean, T\' \u0111\u1ecdc X ch\u01b0a \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c commit.\\n- Non-repeatable reads: read COMMITTED data from an UPDATE query from another transaction, trong c\xf9ng 1 transaction khi READ 1 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb v\xe0 nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c 2 k\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 kh\xe1c nhau.\\n  ![non-repeatable-reads](/img/blogs/iPI0C.png). L\u01b0u \xfd: \u0110\u1ed1i v\u1edbi h\u1ea7u h\u1ebft c\xe1c platform kh\xe1c ngo\u1ea1i tr\u1eeb Postgres. Repeatable read isolation level ch\u1ec9 ch\u1eafc ch\u1eafn l\xe0 n\xf3 ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u1ecdc nh\u1eefng gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb \u0111\xe3 commit m\xe0 kh\xf4ng thay \u0111\u1ed5i. C\xf2n n\u1ebfu x\u1ea3y ra phantom reads th\xec gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb \u0111\u1ea5y v\u1eabn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ecdc.\\n- Phantom reads: read COMMITTED data from an INSERT or DELETE query from another transaction, trong c\xf9ng 1 transaction khi READ l\u1ea7n 1 l\u1ea5y s\u1ed1 l\u01b0\u1ee3ng Product \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c 3, c\xf9ng khi \u0111\xf3 th\xec c\xf3 1 transaction kh\xe1c insert ho\u1eb7c delete 1 products v\xe0 READ l\u1ea7n 2 nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c 1 k\u1ebft qu\u1ea3 kh\xe1c.\\n  ![phantom-read](/img/blogs/aCtew.png).\\n\\n### Isolation levels for inflight transaction: performance s\u1ebd b\u1ecb gi\u1ea3m d\u1ea7n theo c\xe1c levels d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y c\xf2n \u0111\u1ed9 ph\u1ee9c t\u1ea1p th\xec ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i.\\n\\n![Isolation levels vs read phenomena.png](/img/blogs/Isolation_levels_vs_read_phenomena.png)\\n\\n- **Read uncommitted**: No Isolation, t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i t\u1eeb b\xean ngo\xe0i th\xec \u0111\u1ec1u \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c transaction th\u1ea5y.\\n- **Read commited**: M\u1ed7i query trong 1 transaction \u0111\u1ec1u ch\u1ec9 th\u1ea5y nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c committed.\\n- **Repeatable Read**: M\u1ed7i query trong 1 transaction ch\u1ec9 th\u1ea5y nh\u1eefng committed updates tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u transcation.\\n- **Serializable**: Transactions b\u1ecb tu\u1ea7n t\u1ef1 h\xf3a, ngh\u0129a l\xe0 s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi ngay sau transaction tr\u1ee9c ho\xe0n th\xe0nh.\\n\\n## Consistency\\n\\n### Consistency in Dat\\n\\n\u0110\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111i\u1ec1u ch\u1ec9nh b\u1edfi user v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ee7ng c\u1ed1 b\u1eb1ng c\xe1ch th\xeam c\xe1c primary keys, foreign keys.\\n\\nV\xec sao user l\u1ea1i \u0111i\u1ec1u ch\u1ec9nh m\xe0 kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u1eb7t m\u1eb7c \u0111\u1ecbnh l\xfac n\xe0o database c\u0169ng ph\u1ea3i ch\u1eb7t ch\u1ebd, ch\xednh x\xe1c nh\u1ea5t \u2753\\n\\nV\xec \u1edf m\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 tr\u01b0\u1eddng h\u1ee3p th\xec c\xf3 developer c\xf3 th\u1ec3 cho ph\xe9p sai s\u1ed1 nh\u1ecf \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ed5i l\u1ea5y performance.\\n\\n### Consistency in reads\\n\\n1. N\u1ebfu m\u1ed9t transaction change database v\xe0 commit th\xec 1 transaction m\u1edbi c\xf3 ngay l\u1eadp t\u1ee9c th\u1ea5y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c change \u0111\xf3 kh\xf4ng ?\\n\\n- \u0110i\u1ec1u n\xe0y c\xf2n t\xf9y thu\u1ed9c. N\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n ch\u1ec9 d\xf9ng 1 database th\xec \u0111i\u1ec1u \u1edf tr\xean l\xe0 \u0111\xfang. C\xf2n n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n mu\u1ed1n horizontal scale th\xec b\u1eaft bu\u1ed9c b\u1ea1n ph\u1ea3i c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u replica database v\xe0 1 primary database. L\xfac n\xe0y transaction \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c commit s\u1ebd thay \u0111\u1ed5i primary database v\xe0 s\u1ebd m\u1ea5t th\u1eddi gian \u0111\u1ec3 update c\xe1c replica, n\u1ebfu sau khi transaction \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c commit m\xe0 c\xf3 1 transaction m\u1edbi th\u1ef1c hi\u1ec7n vi\u1ec7c read t\u1eeb replica th\xec transaction \u0111\xf3 s\u1ebd nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c data c\u0169.\\n\\n2. C\u1ea3 relational v\xe0 NoSQL database \u0111\u1ec1u b\u1ecb \u1ea3nh h\u01b0\u1edfng.\\n3. \u0110i\u1ec1u n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 eventual consitency.\\n\\n## Durability\\n\\nT\xednh ch\u1ea5t n\xe0y \u0111\u1ea3m b\u1ea3o r\u1eb1ng 1 khi m\xe0 transaction \u0111\xe3 th\u1ef1c thi xong th\xec nh\u1eefng thay \u0111\u1ed5i \u0111\u1ebfn database s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ghi v\xe0o \u1ed5 \u0111\u0129a v\xe0 ch\xfang v\u1eabn s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c d\u1eef ngay c\u1ea3 khi c\xf3 1 l\u1ed7i h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng x\u1ea3y ra ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n nh\u01b0 l\u1ed7i ph\u1ea7n m\u1ec1m ho\u1eb7c l\xe0 m\u1ea5t \u0111i\u1ec7n \ud83d\ude22. (Committed Data is never lost)"},{"id":"snap-in-a-nutshell","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/snap-in-a-nutshell","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-08-23-snap-in-a-nutshell/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-23-snap-in-a-nutshell/index.md","title":"Snap in a nutshell","description":"Snap l\xe0 m\u1ed9t h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng tri\u1ec3n khai v\xe0 \u0111\xf3ng g\xf3i ph\u1ea7n m\u1ec1m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ph\xe1t tri\u1ec3n b\u1edfi Canonical cho nh\u1eefng h\u1ec7 \u0111i\u1ec1u h\xe0nh s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng nh\xe2n Linux.","date":"2021-08-23T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 23, 2021","tags":[{"label":"os","permalink":"/blog/tags/os"},{"label":"snap","permalink":"/blog/tags/snap"}],"readingTime":2.355,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"ACID trong c\u01a1 s\u1edf d\u1eef li\u1ec7u","permalink":"/blog/acid-trong-co-so-du-lieu"},"nextItem":{"title":"C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t docker, nginx, cloudflare, tmate v\xe0 deploy m\u1ed9t web app ho\xe0n to\xe0n free tr\xean raspberry pi","permalink":"/blog/cai-dat-docker-nginx-cloudflare-tmate-va-deploy-mot-web-app-hoan-toan-free-tren-raspberry-pi"}},"content":"Snap l\xe0 m\u1ed9t h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng tri\u1ec3n khai v\xe0 \u0111\xf3ng g\xf3i ph\u1ea7n m\u1ec1m \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ph\xe1t tri\u1ec3n b\u1edfi [Canonical](<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canonical_(company)>) cho nh\u1eefng h\u1ec7 \u0111i\u1ec1u h\xe0nh s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng nh\xe2n Linux.\\n\\n## 1. Why Snap\\n\\nV\u1edbi c\xe1c tr\xecnh qu\u1ea3n l\xfd package kh\xe1c nh\u01b0 `apt` hay `yum` th\xec c\xe1c packages \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\xf3ng g\xf3i v\xe0 ph\xe2n ph\u1ed1i nh\u01b0 1 ph\u1ea7n c\u1ee7a os, \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y t\u1ea1o ra `delay` gi\u1eefa vi\u1ec7c ph\xe1t tri\u1ec3n v\xe0 tri\u1ec3n khai \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ebfn user. Snap \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c sinh ra \u0111\u1ec3 c\xe1c developers c\xf3 th\u1ec3 publish l\xean `Snap Store` v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0a th\u1eb3ng \u0111\u1ebfn ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng.\\n\\n## 2. Ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tr\xean h\u1ea7u h\u1ebft c\xe1c Linux distro\\n\\nM\u1ed9t \u0111\u1eb7c \u0111i\u1ec3m khi\u1ebfn snap ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn l\xe0 c\xe1c `snaps (packages)` c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tr\xean h\u1ea7u h\u1ebft c\xe1c Linux distro.\\n\\nC\xe1c snap \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c n\xe9n v\u1edbi \u0111\u1ecbnh d\u1ea1ng `SquashFS` v\u1edbi \u0111u\xf4i m\u1edf r\u1ed9ng l\xe0 `.snap`. C\xe1c file n\xe0y ch\u1ee9a \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng, c\xe1c dependencies v\xe0 metadata. Metadata \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c bi\xean d\u1ecbch b\u1edfi `snapd` v\xe0 thi\u1ebft l\u1eadp 1 `sandbox` b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt cho \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ea5y. Sau khi snap \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t th\xec n\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c mount t\u1edbi OS host v\xe0 m\u1ed7i khi ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng kh\u1edfi ch\u1ea1y \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng th\xec ch\xfang s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c gi\u1ea3i n\xe9n ngay l\xfac \u0111\u1ea5y, \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y gi\xfap snap s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \xedt dung l\u01b0\u1ee3ng h\u01a1n nh\u01b0ng kh\u1edfi \u0111\u1ed9ng \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng l\u1ea1i l\xe2u h\u01a1n.\\n\\n## 3. C\xe1c snap c\xf3 b\u1ea3o m\u1eadt kh\xf4ng\\n\\nC\xe1c snap \u0111\u1ea9y l\xean Snap Store s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng test v\xe0 scan malware, m\u1eb7c d\xf9 v\u1eady th\xec ch\xfang kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ea1t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ed9 tin c\u1eady nh\u01b0 nh\u1eefng \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng b\xecnh th\u01b0\u1eddng c\u1ee7a distro.\\n\\nV\xe0o th\xe1ng 5(2018), 2 \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ph\xe1t tri\u1ec3n b\u1edfi c\xf9ng 1 developer \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\xecm th\u1ea5y l\xe0 ch\u1ee9a miner ti\u1ec1n \u1ea3o, miner s\u1ebd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1ea1y background khi m\xe0 \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng n\xe0y \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\u1ef1c thi. Khi v\u1ee5 vi\u1ec7c \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c bi\u1ebft \u0111\u1ebfn th\xec Canonical \u0111\xe3 g\u1ee1 2 \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng n\xe0y kh\u1ecfi Snap Store v\xe0 chuy\u1ec3n quy\u1ec1n s\u1edf h\u1eefu \u0111\u1ebfn 1 b\xean th\u1ee9 3 sau khi \u0111\xe3 lo\u1ea1i b\u1ecf miner.\\n\\nM\u1eb7c d\xf9 Snap sandbox \u0111\xe3 gi\u1ea3m \u1ea3nh h\u01b0\u1edfng c\u1ee7a nh\u1eefng \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng x\u1ea5u nh\u01b0ng Canonical v\u1eabn khuy\u1ebfn kh\xedch users ch\u1ec9 n\xean s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng snap c\u1ee7a nh\u1eefng publisher \u0111\xe3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng tin t\u01b0\u1edfng.\\n\\n## 4. C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t snap cho debian\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo apt install snapd\\nsudo snap install core\\n```\\n\\n## 5. T\xecm ki\u1ebfm package\\n\\n```sh\\nsnap find <search_text>\\n```\\n\\n## 6. C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t package b\u1eb1ng snap\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo snap install hugo --channel=extended\\n```\\n\\n## 7. Xem danh s\xe1ch packages\\n\\n```sh\\nsnap list\\n```\\n\\n## 8. G\u1ee1 package c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t b\u1eb1ng snap\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo snap remove <package>\\n```\\n\\n## 9. Update package\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo snap refresh --list\\n```\\n\\n## 10. Snap packages doesn\'t work on zsh or other shell?\\n\\nzsh kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ecdc c\xe1c packages c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t b\u1edfi snap \u1edf th\u01b0 m\u1ee5c `/snap/bin` n\xean ch\xfang ta c\u1ea7n ph\u1ea3i th\xeam `PATH` cho n\xf3 nh\u01b0 sau\\n\\n```sh\\n# .your-zsh-config-folder/.zshrc\\nexport PATH=$PATH:/snap/bin\\n```"},{"id":"cai-dat-docker-nginx-cloudflare-tmate-va-deploy-mot-web-app-hoan-toan-free-tren-raspberry-pi","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/cai-dat-docker-nginx-cloudflare-tmate-va-deploy-mot-web-app-hoan-toan-free-tren-raspberry-pi","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-07-14-cai-dat-docker-nginx-cloudflare-tmate-va-deploy-mot-web-app-hoan-toan-free-tren-raspberry-pi/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-07-14-cai-dat-docker-nginx-cloudflare-tmate-va-deploy-mot-web-app-hoan-toan-free-tren-raspberry-pi/index.md","title":"C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t docker, nginx, cloudflare, tmate v\xe0 deploy m\u1ed9t web app ho\xe0n to\xe0n free tr\xean raspberry pi","description":"1. C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t image cho Pi","date":"2021-07-14T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 14, 2021","tags":[{"label":"tutorial","permalink":"/blog/tags/tutorial"},{"label":"backend","permalink":"/blog/tags/backend"},{"label":"devops","permalink":"/blog/tags/devops"},{"label":"cloudflare","permalink":"/blog/tags/cloudflare"},{"label":"tmate","permalink":"/blog/tags/tmate"},{"label":"raspberry pi","permalink":"/blog/tags/raspberry-pi"}],"readingTime":2.58,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Snap in a nutshell","permalink":"/blog/snap-in-a-nutshell"},"nextItem":{"title":"M\u1ea1ng m\xe1y t\xednh","permalink":"/blog/mang-may-tinh"}},"content":"## 1. C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t image cho Pi\\n\\nC\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t [Raspbian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raspberry_Pi_OS) b\u1eb1ng [raspberry pi imager](https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/)\\n**L\u01b0u \xfd**: Raspberry Pi ch\u1ea1y chip ARM v\xe0 Raspbian \u1edf ki\u1ebfn tr\xfac arm/v7 32bit n\xean c\xe1c c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t \u1edf ph\xeda d\u01b0\u1edbi \u0111\u1ec1u ph\u1ea3i d\xf9ng cho ki\u1ebfn tr\xfac n\xe0y.\\n\\n## 2. C\xe0i tmate \u0111\u1ec3 ssh\\n\\nCh\xfang ta d\xf9ng tmate b\u1ea3n [static build](https://github.com/tmate-io/tmate/releases/tag/2.4.0) arm/v7 32bit \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 \u0111\u1ea7y \u0111\u1ee7 t\xednh n\u0103ng m\u1edbi nh\u1ea5t nh\u01b0 ch\u1ea1y foreground (-F).\\n\\n```sh\\nwget https://github.com/tmate-io/tmate/releases/download/2.4.0/dbg-symbols-tmate-2.4.0-static-linux-arm32v7.tar.xz\\n```\\n\\n\u0110\u0103ng k\xfd API key \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 static IP v\xe0 session name gi\u1ed1ng nhau cho m\u1ed7i l\u1ea7n \u0111\u0103ng nh\u1eadp v\xe0o con Pi.\\nLink \u0111\u0103ng k\xfd \u1edf [\u0111\xe2y](https://tmate.io/#named_sessions) nh\xe9.\\nT\u1ea1o 1 [systemd service](https://github.com/tmate-io/tmate/issues/198) \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ef1 \u0111\u1ed9ng ch\u1ea1y tmate m\u1ed7i l\u1ea7n reboot Pi theo\\n\\n## 3. C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t nginx cho Pi\\n\\nC\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t nginx v\u1edbi apt\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo apt install nginx\\n```\\n\\n## 4. C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t docker v\u1edbi convenience script\\n\\n```sh\\ncurl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh\\nsudo sh get-docker.sh\\n```\\n\\n## 5. Build image cho Pi\\n\\nT\u1ea1o builder\\n\\n```sh\\ndocker buildx create --platform linux/arm/v7 --name armbuilder\\n```\\n\\nS\u1eed d\u1ee5ng builder\\n\\n```sh\\ndocker buildx use armbuilder\\n```\\n\\nBootstrap builder\\n\\n```sh\\ndocker buildx inspect --bootstrap\\n```\\n\\nSau khi \u0111\xe3 c\xf3 builder m\u1edbi ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u build image\\nV\xec \u0111a s\u1ed1 ch\xfang ta kh\xf4ng s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng ki\u1ebfn tr\xfac arm/v7 n\xean ta s\u1ebd c\u1ea7n ph\u1ea3i c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t th\xeam 1 cross-platform emulator cho docker \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 build \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c image cho arm/v7. Xem chi ti\u1ebft \u1edf [\u0111\xe2y](https://github.com/tonistiigi/binfmt#installing-emulators)\\n\\n```sh\\ndocker run --privileged --rm tonistiigi/binfmt --install all\\n```\\n\\nBuild image \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean cho pi\\n\\n```sh\\ndocker buildx build --platform linux/arm/v7 -t ducnguyen96/drinkwater-api:0.0.13 --push .\\n```\\n\\n**L\u01b0u \xfd**: V\u1edbi c\xe1c b\u1ea1n \u0111ang s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng bcrypt cho \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng c\u1ee7a m\xecnh th\xec c\xe1c b\u1ea1n n\xean chuy\u1ec3n sang bcryptjs v\xec bcrypt kh\xf4ng ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tr\xean arm/v7 nh\xe9.\\n\\n## 6. Docker run tr\xean pi\\n\\nC\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u image \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c built based t\u1eeb alpine - 1 phi\xean b\u1ea3n linux tinh g\u1ecdn d\xf9ng v\xe0 ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng ch\xfang r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u. Docker c\xf3 t\xednh n\u0103ng security \u0111\u1ec3 c\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t ch\u1eb7t ch\u1ebd c\xe1c t\xednh to\xe1n tr\xean container, \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ch\u1ea1y t\xednh n\u0103ng n\xe0y tr\xean image Alpine th\xec n\xf3 y\xeau c\u1ea7u libseccomp m\xe0 c\xf3 v\u1ebb nh\u01b0 Alpine c\xf2n thi\u1ebfu, v\u1eady ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd t\u1eaft t\xednh n\u0103ng n\xe0y \u0111i.\\n\\n```sh\\n--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined\\n```\\n\\nTham kh\u1ea3o t\u1ea1i [\u0111\xe2y](https://www.gitmemory.com/issue/Koenkk/zigbee2mqtt/7662/852985841)\\nKh\u1edfi ch\u1ea1y container \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean n\xe0o :3\\n\\n```sh\\ndocker run -it -d --name drinkwate-web --security-opt=seccomp=unconfined\\n-p 4000:4000 ducnguyen96/drinkwater-web:0.0.13\\n```\\n\\n## 7. Self host v\u1edbi cloudflare\\n\\nC\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t cloudflare cho pi \u1edf [\u0111\xe2y](https://docs.pi-hole.net/guides/dns/cloudflared/#armhf-architecture-32-bit-raspberry-pi)\\nL\u01b0u \xfd: Th\u01b0 m\u1ee5c g\u1ed1c c\u1ee7a cloudflare n\u1eb1m \u1edf /etc/cloudflared\\n\\n1. Login\\n\\n```sh\\ncloudflared tunnel login\\n```\\n\\nN\u1ebfu pi ch\u1ec9 ch\u1ea1y terminal th\xec copy link v\xe0o browser nh\xe9\\n\\n2. Create a tunnel\\n\\n```sh\\ncloudflared tunnel create <NAME>\\n```\\n\\n3. Config tunnel\\n\\n```sh\\ntunnel: 6ff42ae2-765d-4adf-8112-31c55c1551ef\\ncredentials-file: /root/.cloudflared/6ff42ae2-765d-4adf-8112-31c55c1551ef.js\\n\\n\\ningress:\\n - hostname: gitlab.widgetcorp.tech\\n service: http://localhost:80\\n - hostname: gitlab-ssh.widgetcorp.tech\\n service: ssh://localhost:22\\n - service: http_status:404\\n```\\n\\n4. Route to tunnel theo m\u1eabu sau\\n   ![dns-record](/img/blogs/dns-record.png)\\n5. Run cloudflare as a service\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo cloudflared service install\\n```\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo systemctl start cloudflared\\n```\\n\\n```sh\\nsudo systemctl enable cloudflared\\n```\\n\\nV\u1eady l\xe0 ch\xfang ta \u0111\xe3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 host 1 web app ho\xe0n to\xe0n free :3 !"},{"id":"mang-may-tinh","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/mang-may-tinh","editUrl":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96/ducnguyen96.github.io/blog/blog/2021-06-25-mang-may-tinh/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-06-25-mang-may-tinh/index.md","title":"M\u1ea1ng m\xe1y t\xednh","description":"Ph\u1ea7n 1 - The TCP/IP Five-Layer Network Model","date":"2021-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 25, 2021","tags":[{"label":"networking","permalink":"/blog/tags/networking"}],"readingTime":10.84,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"\u0110\u1ee9c Nguy\u1ec5n","title":"Developer","url":"https://github.com/ducnguyen96","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47471616?v=4","key":"ducnguyen96"}],"prevItem":{"title":"C\xe0i \u0111\u1eb7t docker, nginx, cloudflare, tmate v\xe0 deploy m\u1ed9t web app ho\xe0n to\xe0n free tr\xean raspberry pi","permalink":"/blog/cai-dat-docker-nginx-cloudflare-tmate-va-deploy-mot-web-app-hoan-toan-free-tren-raspberry-pi"}},"content":"## Ph\u1ea7n 1 - The TCP/IP Five-Layer Network Model\\n\\n![7 layers](/img/docs/layers-responsibility.png)\\nThe protocols at each layer carry the ones above them in order to get data from one place to the next.\\n\\n### 1. Physical Layer\\n\\n\u0110\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho nh\u1eefng thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb v\u1eadt l\xfd k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi m\xe1y t\xednh. Li\xean quan \u0111\u1ebfn nh\u1eefng th\u1ee9 nh\u01b0 c\xe1p, thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i, g\u1eedi t\xedn hi\u1ec7u.\\n\\n### 2. Data Link Layer\\n\\n- The network interface or the network access layer.\\n- L\u1edbp n\xe0y ch\u1ecbu tr\xe1ch nhi\u1ec7m \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a c\xe1c c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ec3 di\u1ec5n d\u1ecbch (interpreting) c\xe1c t\xedn hi\u1ebfu \u0111\u1ec3 cho c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb c\xf3 th\u1ec3 giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau.\\n- C\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u giao th\u1ee9c (protocols) xu\u1ea5t hi\u1ec7n \u1edf layer n\xe0y nh\u01b0ng ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn nh\u1ea5t l\xe0 Ethernet.\\n- C\xe1c ti\xeau chu\u1ea9n c\u1ee7a Ethernet c\u0169ng \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a 1 giao th\u1ee9c ch\u1ecbu tr\xe1ch nhi\u1ec7m cho vi\u1ec7c nh\u1eadn d\u1eef li\u1ec7u t\u1eeb c\xe1c node tr\xean c\xf9ng 1 network.\\n\\n### 3. Internet Layer\\n\\n- Layer n\xe0y cho ph\xe9p c\xe1c network kh\xe1c nhau c\xf3 th\u1ec3 giao ti\u1ebfp \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c v\u1edbi nhau th\xf4ng qua c\xe1c routers.\\n- Giao th\u1ee9c ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn nh\u1ea5t \u1edf layer n\xe0y l\xe0 IP (Internet Protocol).\\n- M\u1ed9t node ri\xeang r\u1ebd c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ch\u1ea1y nhi\u1ec1u \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng clients ho\u1eb7c servers. B\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ch\u1ea1y 1 ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh client email v\xe0 web browser c\xf9ng l\xfac. Email v\xe0 webserver c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ch\u1ea1y tr\xean c\xf9ng 1 server.\\n\\n### 4. Transport Layer\\n\\n- Emails v\xe0 Web pages c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n l\xe0 nh\u1edd transport layer.\\n- Khi Internet Layer chuy\u1ec3n d\u1eef li\u1ec7u gi\u1eefa c\xe1c node \u0111\u1ed9c l\u1eadp. Transport Layer ph\xe2n lo\u1ea1i \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng client ho\u1eb7c server n\xe0o th\xec n\xean nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c data t\u1eeb Internet layer.\\n- Giao th\u1ee9c ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn nh\u1ea5t \u1edf layer n\xe0y l\xe0 TCP (Transmission Control Protocol). 1 s\u1ed1 giao th\u1ee9c kh\xe1c c\xf3 s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ebfn IP c\xf3 th\u1ec3 k\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ebfn nh\u01b0 UDP (User Datagram Protocol).\\n\\n**L\u01b0u \xfd**: IP ch\u1ecbu tr\xe1ch nhi\u1ec7m nh\u1eadn d\u1eef li\u1ec7u t\u1eeb node n\xe0y sang node kh\xe1c, trong khi TCP ho\u1eb7c UDP th\xec ch\u1ecbu tr\xe1ch nhi\u1ec7m ph\xe2n lo\u1ea1i d\u1eef li\u1ec7u nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1eeb IP \u0111\u1ebfn \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng c\u1ea7n thi\u1ebft (applications or programs)\\n\\n## Ph\u1ea7n 2 - The Basics of Networking Devices\\n\\n### 1. Cables\\n\\n- C\xe1p k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i nh\u1eefng thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb kh\xe1c nhau v\xe0 cho ph\xe9p data \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c truy\u1ec1n qua l\u1ea1i gi\u1eefa c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb.\\n- C\xe1p \u0111\u1ed3ng (copper) l\xe0 lo\u1ea1i c\xe1p \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c d\xf9ng ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn nh\u1ea5t. N\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o th\xe0nh t\u1eeb c\xe1c c\u1eb7p d\xe2y \u0111\u1ed3ng v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c b\u1ecdc b\u1edfi d\xe2y d\u1eabn c\xe1ch \u0111i\u1ec7n.\\n- M\xe1y t\xednh giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau b\u1eb1ng 0 v\xe0 1. Ch\xfang g\u1eedi c\xe1c d\u1eef li\u1ec7u nh\u1ecb ph\xe2n b\u1eb1ng c\xe1ch thay \u0111\u1ed5i voltage (\u0111i\u1ec7n th\u1ebf).\\n- Thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\xedn hi\u1ec7u s\u1ebd di\u1ec5n d\u1ecbch c\xe1c thay \u0111\u1ed5i \u0111i\u1ec7n th\u1ebf n\xe0y th\xe0nh 0 v\xe0 1 v\xe0 sau \u0111\xf3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c chuy\u1ec3n th\xe0nh c\xe1c d\u1ea1ng d\u1eef li\u1ec7u kh\xe1c nhau.\\n- C\xe1c lo\u1ea1i ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn nh\u1ea5t: Cat5, Cat5e, Cat6. Nh\u1eefng lo\u1ea1i n\xe0y th\xec c\xf3 c\xe1c \u0111\u1eb7c \u0111i\u1ec3m v\u1eadt l\xfd kh\xe1c nhau, ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n s\u1ed1 l\u1ea7n xo\u1eafn gi\u1eefa c\xe1c c\u1eb7p d\xe2y \u0111\u1ed3ng d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn vi\u1ec7c thay \u0111\u1ed5i chi\u1ec1u d\xe0i c\xe1p c\u0169ng nh\u01b0 t\u1ec9 l\u1ec7 truy\u1ec1n t\u1ea3i.\\n- Cat5 l\xe0 lo\u1ea1i c\u0169 nh\u1ea5t v\xe0 g\u1ea7n nh\u01b0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thay th\u1ebf b\u1eb1ng Cat5e v\xe0 Cat6.\\n\\n### 2. Hub\\n\\n- Hub l\xe0 thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb \u1edf physical layer cho ph\xe9p nhi\u1ec1u k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i c\xf9ng 1 l\xfac \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1eeb nhi\u1ec1u m\xe1y t\xednh.\\n- C\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ebfn 1 hub n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 s\u1ebd giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau c\xf9ng l\xfac. T\xf9y thu\u1ed9c v\xe0o c\xe1c h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i c\u1ee7a c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb m\xe0 ch\xfang s\u1ebd quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh xem data \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c truy\u1ec1n \u0111\u1ebfn c\xf3 ph\u1ea3i d\xe0nh cho ch\xfang hay kh\xf4ng. \u0110i\u1ec1u n\xe3y d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn c\xf3 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u noise tr\xean network v\xe0 g\xe2y ra 1 v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 collision domain.\\n\\n### 3. Collision Domain\\n\\n![Collision Domain](/img/docs/collision-domain.png)\\nMany or all devices on a network shared a single collision domain. All data in collision domain is snet to all the nodes connected to it.\\n\\nCollision Domain l\xe0 1 network segment (ph\xe2n \u0111o\u1ea1n) n\u01a1i c\xf9ng l\xfac ch\u1ec9 1 thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb c\xf3 th\u1ec3 giao ti\u1ebfp. N\u1ebfu nhi\u1ec1u h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng c\u1ed1 truy\u1ec1n d\u1eef li\u1ec7u c\xf9ng l\xfac th\xec c\xe1c xung \u0111i\u1ec7n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi trong s\u1ee3i c\xe1p s\u1ebd g\xe2y tr\u1edf ng\u1ea1i cho nhau. Vi\u1ec7c n\xe0y d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn vi\u1ec7c c\xe1c h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi hub ph\u1ea3i ch\u1edd 1 th\u1eddi gian tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi ch\xfang c\u1ed1 t\xe1i g\u1eedi d\u1eef li\u1ec7u. Ch\xednh v\xec v\u1eady m\xe0 m\u1ea1ng l\u01b0\u1edbi r\u1ea5t ch\u1eadm n\xean g\u1ea7n nh\u01b0 ng\xe0y n\xe0y ch\xfang ta kh\xf4ng c\xf2n s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng hub n\u1eefa v\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c thay th\u1ebf b\u1eb1ng switch.\\n\\n### 4. Switching Hub\\n\\n- Switch r\u1ea5t gi\u1ed1ng Hub \u1edf ch\u1ed7 ch\xfang cho ph\xe9p r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ebfn ch\xfang. \u0110i\u1ec3m kh\xe1c bi\u1ec7t l\xe0 Hub th\xec \u1edf layer 1 (Physical Layer) c\xf2n switch th\xec \u1edf layer 2 (Data Link Layer).\\n- Switch c\xf3 th\u1ec3 inspect (quan s\xe1t) n\u1ed9i dung b\xean trong d\u1eef li\u1ec7u c\u1ee7a giao th\u1ee9c ethernet \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi trong to\xe0n m\u1ea1ng. V\xe0 quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh xem d\u1eef li\u1ec7u n\xean \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng n\xe0o v\xe0 ch\u1ec9 g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn h\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng \u0111\xf3. Switch g\u1ea7n nh\u01b0 l\u1ecdai b\u1ecf ho\xe0n to\xe0n collision domain.\\n\\n### 5. Routers\\n\\n- Hubs v\xe0 Switches \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 cho c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb c\xf3 th\u1ec3 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ebfn c\xf9ng 1 m\u1ea1ng l\u01b0\u1edbi c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 (LAN - Local Area Network), \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 truy\u1ec1n nh\u1eadn d\u1eef li\u1ec7u t\u1eeb c\xe1c network th\xec ch\xfang ta c\u1ea7n \u0111\u1ebfn router.\\n- Router l\xe0 1 thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb cho ph\xe9p truy\u1ec1n t\u1ea3i d\u1eef li\u1ec7u gi\u1eefa c\xe1c networks. Router ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng \u1edf layer 3.\\n- Switch c\xf3 inspect d\u1eef li\u1ec7u Ethernet \u0111\u1ec3 quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh ch\xfang \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn \u0111\xe2u, Router th\xec c\xf3 th\u1ec3 inspect d\u1eef li\u1ec7u IP \u0111\u1ec3 quy\u1ebft \u0111\u1ecbnh ch\xfang \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn \u0111\xe2y.\\n- Nh\u1eefng routers m\xe0 ta th\u01b0\u1eddng th\u1ea5y l\xe0 nh\u1eefng home routers, b\u1ea3ng routing table c\u1ee7a ch\xfang kh\xe1 \u0111\u01a1n gi\u1ea3n. M\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch c\u1ee7a ch\xfang l\xe0 nh\u1eadn traffic t\u1eeb home ho\u1eb7c office v\xe0 g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ebfn ISP (Internet Service Provider).\\n- M\u1ed9t khi traffic \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi \u0111\xean ISP th\xec 1 lo\u1ea1i router m\u1edbi ph\u1ee9c t\u1ea1p h\u01a1n nhi\u1ec1u nh\u1eadn nhi\u1ec7m v\u1ee5 x\u1eed l\xfd traffic. Nh\u1eefng core ISP router n\xe0y ch\u1ecbu tr\xe1ch nhi\u1ec7m cho vi\u1ec7c g\u1eedi v\xe0 nh\u1eadn d\u1eef li\u1ec7u h\u1eb1ng ng\xe0y tr\xean internet c\u1ee7a ch\xfang ta.\\n- Routers chia s\u1ebb d\u1eef li\u1ec7u v\u1edbi nhau qua giao th\u1ee9c BGP (Border Gateway Protocol). Giao th\u1ee9c n\xe0y cho bi\u1ebft \u0111o\u1ea1n \u0111\u01b0\u1eddng t\u1ed1i \u01b0u nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec3 truy\u1ec1n traffic.\\n\\n### 6. Servers and Clients\\n\\n- Ch\xfang ta g\u1ecdi m\u1ed7i thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb tr\xean network l\xe0 1 nodes. 1 nodes c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0 1 server hay l\xe0 1 client ho\u1eb7c th\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0 v\u1eeba server v\xe0 client. 1 server l\xe0 1 node m\xe0 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 cung c\u1ea5p d\u1eef li\u1ec7u cho 1 client n\xe0o \u0111\xf3, v\xe0 client ch\xednh l\xe0 node nh\u1eadn d\u1eef li\u1ec7u.\\n- Ch\u1eb3ng h\u1ea1n email server v\u1eeba c\xf3 th\u1ec3 xem l\xe0 1 server v\xec ch\xfang g\u1eedi email \u0111\u1ebfn \u1ee9ng d\u1ee5ng email c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi d\xf9ng. Nh\u01b0ng c\u0169ng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 xem n\xf3 l\xe0 1 client c\u1ee7a DNS server.\\n\\n## Ph\u1ea7n 3 - The Data Link Layer\\n\\n![5-layers](/img/docs/layers-responsibility.png)\\nBy dumping responsibility on the Data Link Layer, the Network, Transport, Application layers can all operate the same no matter how the device they\'re running on is connected.\\n\\n### 1. Ethernet and MAC address\\n\\n- Giao th\u1ee9c \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng r\u1ed9ng r\xe3i nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec3 truy\u1ec1n d\u1eef li\u1ec7u gi\u1eefa c\xe1c links \u0111\u1ed9c l\u1eadp l\xe0 Ethernet. Data Link Layer cung c\u1ea5p 1 c\xe1ch chung \u0111\u1ec3 sofware \u1edf c\xe1c layer cao h\u01a1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 truy\u1ec1n v\xe0 nh\u1eadn d\u1eef li\u1ec7u.\\n- MAC address l\xe0 1 \u0111\u1ecbnh danh \u0111\u1ed9c nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eafn v\u1edbi 1 network interface. L\xe0 1 d\xe3y s\u1ed1 48 bit g\u1ed3m 6 c\u1eb7p s\u1ed1 hexadecimal(16 bits), 1 c\xe1ch kh\xe1c n\u1eefa \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ecbnh danh MAC l\xe0 Octet.\\n\\n### 2. Unicast, Multicast and Broadcast\\n\\n- Unicast frame: lu\xf4n g\u1eedi t\u1edbi t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb tr\xean collision domain nh\u01b0ng ch\u1ec9 th\u1ee5c s\u1ef1 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c nh\u1eadn v\xe0 x\u1eed l\xfd b\u1edfi 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9.\\n- Multicast frame: g\u1eedi t\u1edbi t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3, nh\u01b0ng nh\u1eadn ho\u1eb7c lo\u1ea1i b\u1ecf th\xec t\xf9y v\xe0o t\u1eebng thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb.\\n- Broadcast frame\\n\\n### 3. Dissecting an Ethernet Frame\\n\\n- Data packet l\xe0 1 thu\u1eadt ng\u1eefa bao tr\xf9m \u0111\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho b\u1ea5t k\u1ef3 1 b\u1ed9 d\u1eef li\u1ec7u nh\u1ecb ph\xe2n n\xe0o \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c truy\u1ec1n trong network. Data packet kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eafn v\u1edbi 1 layer c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 n\xe0o.\\n- Data packet \u1edf Ethernet level \u0111\u01b0u\u1ecdc bi\u1ebft nh\u01b0 c\xe1c Ethernet frame.\\n- Ethernet Frame l\xe0 1 b\u1ed9 s\u01b0u t\u1eadp th\xf4ng tin c\u1ea5u tr\xfac cao \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c tr\xecnh b\xe0y trong 1 tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3. Nh\u01b0 v\u1eady, c\xe1c network interfaces \u1edf physical layer c\xf3 th\u1ec3 chuy\u1ec3n 1 d\xe3y bits th\xe0nh d\u1eef li\u1ec7u c\xf3 \xfd ngh\u0129a v\xe0 ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i.\\n  ![ethernet-frame](/img/docs/ethernet-frame.png)\\n\\n  C\xe1c segment trong Ethernet Frame l\xe0 kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 thi\u1ebfu v\xe0 h\u1ea7u nh\u01b0 l\xe0 c\xf3 k\xedch th\u01b0\u1edbc c\u1ed1 \u0111\u1ecbnh.\\n\\n- 7 bytes \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ed3ng b\u1ed9 internal clocks \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111i\u1ec3u ch\u1ec9nh t\u1ed1c \u0111\u1ed9 truy\u1ec1n t\u1ea3i d\u1eef li\u1ec7u.\\n- 1 bytes ti\u1ebfp theo (SFD - Start Frame Delimiter) g\u1eedi t\xedn hi\u1ec7u r\u1eb1ng preamable \u0111\xe3 k\u1ebft th\xfac v\xe0 frame b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u ngay sau \u0111\xf3.\\n- 6 bytes ti\u1ebfp l\xe0 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC.\\n- EtherType filed: d\xe0i 16 bits \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 mi\xeau t\u1ea3 giao th\u1ee9c c\u1ee7a n\u1ed9idung c\u1ee7a frame.\\n- VLAN: b\u1ea5t c\u1ee9 frame n\xe0o c\xf3 VLAN tag th\xec ch\u1ec9 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1edbi 1 ... c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3.\\n\\n## Ph\u1ea7n 4 - The Network Layer\\n\\n### 1. The Network Layer\\n\\nTrong m\u1ea1ng LAN th\xec c\xe1c nodes \u0111\u1ec1u ch\u1ec9 giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau trong 1 m\u1ea1ng nh\u1ecf th\xf4ng qua c\xe1c c\xe1p n\xean \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\xe1p \u1ee9ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c nh\u01b0 c\u1ea7u. Nh\u01b0ng c\xf3 h\xe0ng t\u1ef7 c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb tr\xean th\u1ebf gi\u1edbi c\xf3 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC \u0111\u1ed9c l\u1eadp v\xe0 ch\xfang kh\xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eafp x\u1ebfp theo 1 tr\xecnh t\u1ef1 c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3 n\xe0o n\xean vi\u1ec7c giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi nhau \u1edf m\u1ea1ng l\u01b0\u1edbi to\xe0n c\u1ea7u s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC l\xe0 r\u1ea5t kh\xf3 kh\u0103n. Ch\xednh v\xec th\u1ebf IP sinh ra \u0111\u1ec3 gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 n\xe0y.\\n\\n### 2. IP Addresses\\n\\n![ip-addresses](/img/docs/ip-address.png)\\nIP l\xe0 c\xe1c gi\xe3y s\u1ed1 d\xe0i 32 bit \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c t\u1ea1o h\xe0nh t\u1eeb 4 octet. M\u1ed7i octet c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ea1i di\u1ec7n cho m\u1ecdi s\u1ed1 trong kho\u1ea3ng t\u1eeb 0 \u0111\u1ebfn 255.\\n\\n\u2139\ufe0f **Ch\xfa \xfd**: C\xe1c \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP thu\u1ed9c v\u1ec1 networks ch\u1ee9 kh\xf4ng thu\u1ed9c v\u1ec1 c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi network. Laptop c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd lu\xf4n c\xf3 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC duy nh\u1ea5t t\u1eeb khi s\u1ea3n xu\u1ea5t nh\u01b0ng s\u1ebd c\xf3 IP kh\xe1c nhau l\xfac b\u1ea1n \u0111i cafe, l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c \u1edf nh\xe0, c\xf4ng ty,... M\u1ea1ng LAN \u1edf cafe, home, c\xf4ng ty s\u1ebd cung c\u1ea5p 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP t\u1edbi laptop c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n b\u1eb1ng 1 c\xf4ng ngh\u1ec7 g\u1ecdi l\xe0 DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)\\n\\n- 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5p b\u1eb1ng DHCP \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 Dynamic IP address (\u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP \u0111\u1ed9ng), tr\xe1i ng\u01b0\u1ee3c v\u1edbi Static IP address l\xe0 (\u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP t\u0129nh) \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea5u h\xecnh tr\xean 1 node th\u1ee7 c\xf4ng.\\n- Trong h\u1ea7u h\u1ebft c\xe1c tr\u01b0\u1eddng h\u1ee3p th\xec IP t\u0129nh \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c d\xf9ng cho servers v\xe0 c\xe1c thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb mang, IP \u0111\u1ed9ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c d\xf9ng cho clients. Nh\u01b0ng trong 1 s\u1ed1 tr\u01b0\u1eddng h\u1ee3p th\xec c\xf3 th\u1ec3 kh\xf4ng \u0111\xfang.\\n\\n### 3. IP Datagrams and Encapsulation\\n\\n![data-gram](/img/docs/datagram.png)\\nGi\u1ed1ng nh\u01b0 data packets \u1edf Ethernet layer c\xf3 1 c\xe1i t\xean ri\xeang - Ethernet Frame th\xec c\xe1c packets \u1edf Network layer c\u0169ng v\u1eady - IP datagram - l\xe0 1 d\xe3y c\xe1c tr\u01b0\u1eddng c\xf3 c\u1ea5u tr\xfac cao \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a 1 c\xe1ch ch\u1eb7t ch\u1ebd.\\n![data-encapsulated](/img/docs/datagram-encapsulated.png)\\nContents c\u1ee7a IP datagram \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\xf3ng g\xf3i th\xe0nh payload c\u1ee7a 1 Ethernet Frame. V\xe0 IP datagram c\u0169ng c\xf3 payload \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi xu\u1ed1ng t\u1eeb Transport layer.\\n\\n### 4. IP Address Classes\\n\\n![ip-addresses](/img/docs/ip-addresses.png)\\nClass A c\xf3 3 bits cho IP address. M\u1ed7i octet c\xf3 gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb t\u1eeb 0 \u0111\u1ebfn 255 n\xean s\u1ebd c\xf3 t\u1ed5ng c\u1ed9ng 256*256*256=16777216 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP cho m\u1ed7i host class A\\n\\n- \u0110\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP c\xf3 th\u1ec3 chia l\xe0m 2 ## ph\u1ea7n l\xe0 address ID v\xe0 host ID.\\n- IP c\xf3 3 classes: Class A(1 octets \u0111\u1ea7u l\xe0 address ID, 3 octet ti\u1ebfp l\xe0 host ID), class B (2 octet \u0111\u1ea7u l\xe0 address ID), class C (1 octet l\xe0 address ID).\\n- \u1ede class D, m\u1ed7i 1 IP datagram c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1eedi t\u1edbi to\xe0n b\u1ed9 network c\xf9ng 1 l\xfac.\\n\\n### 5. ARP - Address Resolution Protocol\\n\\nARP l\xe0 m\u1ed9t giao th\u1ee9c \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c s\u1eed d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ec3 t\xecm ra \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 ## ph\u1ea7n c\u1ee9ng c\u1ee7a 1 node v\u1edbi 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP c\u1ee5 th\u1ec3. Khi m\xe0 IP datagram \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c h\xecnh th\xe0nh 1 c\xe1ch ho\xe0n to\xe0n th\xec n\xf3 c\u1ea7n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c \u0111\xf3ng g\xf3i trong 1 Ethernet Frame. Ngh\u0129a l\xe0 thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb truy\u1ec1n t\xedn hi\u1ec7u c\u1ea7n 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC \u0111\u1ec3 c\xf3 th\u1ec3 ho\xe0n th\xe0nh header trong Ethernet Frame.\\n![send-abroad](/img/docs/sending-arp-broadcast.png)\\n\\nKhi mu\u1ed1n g\u1eedi ethernet frame \u0111\u1ebfn 1 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 IP n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 m\xe0 ch\u01b0a c\xf3 \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC th\xec thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb g\u1eedi s\u1ebd truy\u1ec1n \u0111i 1 ARP message broadcast \u0111\u1ebfn to\xe0n b\u1ed9 c\xe1c node tr\xean network.\\n![arp-response](/img/docs/arp-response.png)\\n\\nC\xe1c node khi nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c arp message s\u1ebd ph\u1ea3n h\u1ed3i v\xe0 g\u1eedi \u0111\u1ecba ch\u1ec9 MAC \u0111\u1ebfn thi\u1ebft b\u1ecb g\u1eedi. Sau \u0111\xf3 ARP s\u1ebd c\u1eadp nh\u1eadt MAC address v\xe0o ARP table entries. C\xe1c entries n\xe0y s\u1ebd h\u1ebft h\u1ea1n trong 1 kho\u1ea3ng th\u1eddi gian ng\u1eafn."}]}')}}]);